title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apples, and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place sliced apples on top.
Sprinkle apples with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball with raspberry preserves
directions: Grate American and Cheddar cheese. Mix in pecan chips, chopped green onions and enough mayonnaise to hold together mold. Refrigerate until ready to use, then unmold on tray and cover with raspberry preserves. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: microwave creamy fudge
directions: Grease an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking pan.
Mix sugar, milk, butter or margarine and salt in a 3-quart microwave-safe bowl. Cover loosely with waxed paper and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, until mixture begins to boil.
Uncover and microwave on High for 10 minutes longer, stirring every 3 minutes.

Then continue to microwave for 4 to 8 more minutes, stirring every 2 minutes, until instant read or microwave candy thermometer registers 234° to 240° (soft ball stage) or a small amount dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball that flattens when removed from water.
Then stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla until marshmallows and chocolate are melted.
Add nuts, stirring vigorously until mixture is creamy and slightly glossy.
Spread in prepared pan.
Refrigerate for about 2 hours, until firm.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 25 delicious bars.

title: creamed peas and potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan. Cover with water and cook until tender. Cook peas according to package directions, adding sugar.

title: low calorie pizza
directions: Cut the pita bread around the circular diameter to make two pizza crusts.
Spread spaghetti sauce on top of pita crusts.
Add low-fat or no-fat Mozzarella cheese.
Add vegetable toppings to taste.
Bake in oven at 400° until cheese melts or crust is crispy.
Enjoy.

title: italian rice meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef and next 8 ingredients.
Form into 18 meatballs, approximately 2-inches in diameter, and chill for 30 minutes.

title: fiesta appetizer
directions: Spray a 13 1/2-inch cake pan with Pam.
Layer jalapenos so you have one per serving.
Layer all cheese on top of jalapenos.
Pour beaten eggs over the top of the cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes (side of pan should start turning brown).
Let cool for 15 minutes before cutting.
Serve warm.

title: vidalia onion soup au gratin
directions: Butter the French bread slices and toast until golden brown. In heavy-bottom Dutch oven, melt butter (medium-high). Add onions and saute until caramelized (approximately 30 minutes).
Add sausage and garlic; stir for 5 minutes.
Add flour and stir well. Add stock slowly (may use six 10 ounce cans broth).
Bring to a rolling boil, reduce to simmer and cook for 45 minutes.
Add wine and salt and pepper to taste.
Add green onions and parsley; cook 5 to 10 minutes more.
Preheat broiler.
Ladle soup in bowls; top with bread and cheese.
Broil until cheese bubbles.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: black bean soup(crock-pot)
directions: Cook in crock-pot until carrots are tender. Add cooked rice and continue cooking until warmed through.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onions in pot.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and spices to taste.
Simmer about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: glorified sauerkraut
directions: Saute the butter, onions, green pepper and mushrooms.
Combine with the sauerkraut and tomatoes in a casserole and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour, then for 1/2 hour, uncovered.
May be prepared a day or so in advance of serving, then reheated.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix the milk and vinegar.
Blend the flour, Crisco and salt. Mix in the milk.
Chill.
This is great; makes a light pie crust for 1 pie.

title: cranberry corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift together into a large bowl the corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add and mix only enough to dampen completely the oil, egg, milk, cranberry sauce and grated rind of the orange.
Bake in a greased 8-inch square pan for 25 minutes.

title: butterscotch pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add slightly beaten eggs, pecans, butterscotch chips, vanilla and butter. Mix well. Pour into frozen pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 325° until lightly brown.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add milk, water and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1/2 cup rice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook 1 hour on medium flame.
Stir after 1 hour.
Mix in bowl the milk, egg, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in pot. Cooks until boils.
Put in bowl and cover.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix well and chill before serving.

title: custard pound cake
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Blend in flour. Add flavoring. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and	hot water.
Add bananas, pineapple with juice, strawberries and pecans.
Put 1/2 of mixture in pan and chill until set.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Heat soup, milk, onion and salt on low heat in large saucepan on top of stove.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Add potatoes to hot soup mixture.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread over crust.
Top with tiny pieces of broccoli, cauliflower and grated carrot.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella.
Chill.
Cut into small squares to serve.

title: hot rolls or doughnuts
directions: Pour hot water over shortening. Mix yeast in warm water and dissolve well. Add sugar and then eggs. Mix salt in flour. Add flour last. Let rise in warm place covered with cloth. Work down. This can be kept in refrigerator several days. Take out to use for rolls or doughnuts. Store back in refrigerator.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Roll pork chops in pepper and cracker crumbs.
Brown a little. Place chops on top of cooked rice in a covered dish.
Spoon soup over pork chops and rice.
Place in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix together all ingredients at room temperature.
Roll into tiny balls.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, or until tops are golden.
These may be frozen before baking and kept up to one month in freezer.
Makes 70 balls.

title: mushroom-stuffed tenderloin
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove. Crumble and set aside. Drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings. In drippings, saute mushrooms, onion and garlic until tender. Remove from heat. Stir in 1/2 cup of bread crumbs, parsley and bacon. Cut a slit lengthwise 3/4 of way through the tenderloin. Lightly place stuffing in the pocket. Close with toothpicks. Combine butter and Parmesan cheese. Spread over top and sides of meat. Press remaining bread crumbs onto butter mixture. Place meat on a rack in shallow roasting pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes. Cover and bake for 1 hour or desired doneness. Let stand for 10 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In medium saucepan, heat water and margarine to boiling.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook over medium heat until mixture leaves sides of pan in smooth compact ball, about 2 minutes, stirring vigorously.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating vigorously after each until mixture is smooth and glossy.
Do not underbeat.

title: applesauce prune cake
directions: Stir together the dry ingredients and set aside.
In separate bowl, combine the oil, applesauce and eggs.
Stir in dried ingredients.
Pour into well-buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Dump pie filling in pan.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar, flour and milk.
Pour this over pie filling.
Mix 2 cups sugar and water and pour over the batter.
Bake about 1 hour at 375°.

title: applesauce-oat muffins
directions: Grease 12 muffin cups. Mix crushed cereal, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda. Stir in remaining ingredients
just until moistened. Divide batter evenly among muffin cups. Bake until golden brown, 18 to 22 minutes, at 350°.

title: hasty fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk together well. Dot pan with butter and pour mixture into pan.
Lay fruit on top evenly.
Then pour juice over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Crust will cover cobbler.

title: fruit cake drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat after each addition.
Sift flour and measure; add soda and nutmeg to above mixture alternating with the milk.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Chop pecans and cut fruit into small pieces (mix).
Add 1/2 cup flour and dredge.
Add nuts and fruit to batter and mix well. Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 7 dozen.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa, butter together and boil for 1 minute. Pour remaining ingredients into boiled mixture.
Mix and drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter slightly in 10-inch skillet.
Spread sugar over butter, then place fruit and nuts, with a cherry in the center of each slice of pineapple, to form pleasing design.
Beat egg yolks. Add sugar, juice, flour and baking powder.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 10-inch skillet for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni appetizers
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Stir cheese well.
Add soup and stir again.
Add chopped pepperoni and stir.
Place 1 teaspoon of mixture on slice of bread.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 48.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potato and boil until tender; drain.
Mash.
Work in sugar until stiff and no more sugar can be worked in.
Roll between wax paper thin, like pie crust.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up as jelly roll.
Chill well.
Slice into pieces.

title: our favorite southern pecan pie
directions: Arrange pecan halves in bottom of pie shell.
Beat egg; add butter, corn syrup and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Combine sugar and flour and blend with egg mixture.
Pour over pecan shells.
Let set until nuts rise to the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into baked pie crusts and chill.
Add 1 Cool Whip. Makes 2 pies.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Grease 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Place croutons in baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over croutons.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, mustard, onion powder and pepper; mix until blended.
Pour over croutons and cheese.
Cut each slice of bacon into 5 pieces, cook until crisp; drain.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until eggs are set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in frying pan (cast-iron, better).
Add onions and rice and saute until slightly brown.
Transfer to 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add beef consomme soup and mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until liquid is gone.

title: fluffy cocoa frosting
directions: Note:
For variation, add 1/4 teaspoon almond extract, omitting cocoa powder.
Or omit cocoa powder only for Vanilla Frosting.

title: microwave shrimp scampi
directions: Better than all the seasoning and appetizers in the world, is love with breakfast, lunch and dinner.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all the ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
You can add blueberries to this if you like.
Bake until golden brown, about 8 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Place in
saucepan
and cook over direct heat, stirring until small
amount
dropped
in cold water forms a firm ball. Remove from
heat	and
add
teaspoons	butter,
1 teaspoon vanilla and nuts. Beat until creamy.

title: southern style creamed corn
directions: Cook corn until just barely tender.
Mix butter, flour, sugar and salt in skillet.
Gradually add 1 cup milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add corn.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: danish meatballs
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together. Roll into 1-inch balls. Roll the meatballs in the flour; brown.
Dissolve the bouillon cube in the boiling water.
Pour over the meatballs.
Simmer gently 1 hour.
Add the bay leaf during the last 10 minutes of cooking.
Add water as necessary during simmering to make a delicious gravy.
Remove leaf before serving.

title: traditional "imes" christmas jello
directions: When each dish of Jell-O is firm, cut into pieces and blend in large dish.
Drain and spread 1 can fruit cocktail on top of Jell-O.
Cover with marshmallow which has been blended into very small amount of warm milk.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: white chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt chocolate with hot water in top of double boiler.
Let cool.
Mix Crisco and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cooled chocolate.
Add flour and milk alternately, flour being added first and last.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 300° in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli flowerets into bite size pieces. Chop onion. Combine broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon.
Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar together and pour over the other ingredietns. Mix well. Chill for at least 1 hour and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Sift soda and flour together.
Add dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture.
Make dough.
Roll out and cut, the thinner the better.
Bake at 325° on a greased pan until brown.

title: almond chicken
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: snow balls cookie(also known as mexican wedding cakes)
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and vanilla together. Then add flour and salt. Mix thoroughly. Mix in walnuts. Make 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until bottom of cookie is brown. Remove from cookie sheets; cool. Just before serving, roll cookies in powdered sugar to cover. Yummy.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Put into bottom of square baking dish. Put drained Veg-All on top of the meat and onion.
Spread chicken soup on top of Veg-All.
Put 4 slices of cheese on top of soup, then put Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: my grandma's hermits
directions: In large bowl, mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses. In medium bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt, cloves, ginger and cinnamon. Gradually add dry mixture to large bowl. Add 5 tbsp. water. Add raisins and nuts. Mix all together. Then divide dough into 4 sections. Form each section into a long roll. Place 2 rolls on a greased cookie sheet. Flatten each roll a little bit. Bake at 375° for 20 min. Cool and cut into squares. Repeat for other 2 rolls. Makes 2 1\2 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix together well all ingredients except dough. Set aside. Slice cookie dough rolls into 1/3-inch slices. Place slices of one roll into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press together to cover up any holes. Spoon in cream cheese mixture evenly and top with slices of remaining package of cookie dough.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden and center is slightly firm. Remove from oven and let cool. Refrigerate.
Slice when completely cool.
Enjoy!

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt into bowl. Chip butter into flour and cut until it resembles course meal.
Add buttermilk and mix until it forms a ball.
Pat onto waxed paper, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on baking sheet. Preheat oven to 450° and bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter, jam or honey.

title: molded salad
directions: Mix the water with the jello and immediately stir in 1 pint of vanilla ice cream, then add a large can of crushed pineapple (or any fruit you wish).
Put in a mold to harden.
This sets very quickly.

title: pineapple-bacon coleslaw
directions: Combine green cabbage, red cabbage and salad dressing.
Cover; chill.
Just before serving, add pineapple, carrot and bacon.
Mix lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chess pie cookies
directions: Mix margarine, cake mix and 1 egg; spread evenly in an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs; then spread over crust in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set.

title: pineapple sticky buns
directions: Combine pineapple, butter, sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Spoon into 10 muffin cups.
Place biscuits on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; invert pan to remove biscuits.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Stir in pineapple.
Add flour that has been sifted with baking powder. Mix well.
Spread into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Add topping.

title: quick and easy krispie treats
directions: Using low heat and stirring constantly, melt the butter and marshmallows in skillet.
Turn off heat and stir in vanilla.
Fold in the cereal until it is completely coated.
Spread the cereal mixture in the baking pan.
Cut into squares after the mixture cools.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Combine vinegar and sugar in a saucepan. Heat until sugar is dissolved. Cool and add salt and pepper to taste.

Drain beans to remove juices. Combine remaining ingredients. Marinate with vinegar/sugar mixture several hours or overnight. Kept under refrigeration, this salad will remain good for a week. Serves 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute pepper (green), onion, garlic and beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: buttermilk chocolate brownies
directions: Heat to boil water and butter.
Pour over dry ingredients. Blend well and add the eggs and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Bake for 20 minutes in a greased and floured rather large cookie sheet or large shallow cake pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown on top.

title: ham and cheese pie(swedish pie)
directions: Shred the cheese. Chop the ham.
Wash the leek and cut it into small pieces.
Put some water with a little salt and pepper to boil.
When hot, put the leek in the water to soften.
Take out the pie shells.
Put cheese, ham, and leek in it, in the order written.
Mix eggs and milk. Put a little pepper and salt in it. Pour the milk mixture in the pies to cover the ingredients.
Cook in the oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add mashed bananas.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour mixture into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about one hour.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix eggs, sugar and 3 tablespoons flour until well blended.
Add lemon juice and mix well.
Pour over baked crust and bake again for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sift powdered sugar over bars.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: easy moist brownie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10 x 15-inch sheet cake pan.
In a bowl, beat the dry cake mix, cherry pie mix and eggs until well mixed and stir in nuts, if used.
Dump into pan and bake until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: mexican brunch breakfast
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking dish.
Arrange chilies on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle tomatoes and cheese over it.
Put meat on top of cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Bake until knife comes out clean.

title: light fruitcake
directions: Sift sugar; cream sugar with butter and beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift and measure flour.
Resift with baking powder. Add grated rinds and extracts to creamed mixture.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries with part of flour mixture.
Add remainder of flour and baking powder mixture to cake mixture and stir until smooth. Fold in nuts and cherries.
Add 3/8 teaspoon salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Fold in beaten egg whites in cake mixture.
Bake in a 10-inch tube cake pan at 250° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: tex mex(a crowd pleaser at st. peter's st. patrick's day open!)
directions: Mash avocados, salt and lemon juice; set aside.
Mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning mix; set aside.
Layer bean dip, avocado mix, sour cream mix, green onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve with taco chips.
Makes an 8 x 11-inch pan of dip!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli
in
boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix all ingredients
in
2 quart casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: never fail custard
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt together.
Slowly add milk and vanilla. Bake at 350° until firm.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top while warm.

title: turkey & beer chili
directions: 1. Brown the ground turkey, then add onion and garlic and slightly brown.
2. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a light simmer.
Add water if too thick or simmer if too watery to make
desired consistency.

title: crunchy vegetable salad
directions: Soften gelatine in 1 cup cold water and set aside.
Combine 3/4 cup water, salt, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Add softened gelatine and stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially thickened.
Stir in other ingredients and chill until firm.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: you name it!
directions: Brown onion, garlic, pepper and meat in oil.
Add water, corn and soups and half cheese.
Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Combine with sauce.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 300° until cheese melts. Serve hot and enjoy!
Yields 8 to 10 servings.
This recipe can be halved or doubled according to your crowd!

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt margarine; mix with crumbs and set aside.
Mix Dream Whip with softened cream cheese, milk and sugar.
Use layer of crumbs, layer of Dream Whip mix, layer of pie filling and crumbs on top. Chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in pot.
Pour in corn syrup.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Allow to slightly cool.
Pour in slightly beaten eggs.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 50 minutes or until done (inserted toothpick should come out clean).

title: roasted pork
directions: Place all ingredients, except roast, in a large skillet. Saute about 4 minutes over high heat, stirring occasionally. Cool. Place the roast in a baking pan, fat side up.
Make several large slits in the meat with a knife, being careful not to cut through to the bottom.
Stuff the pockets with some of the vegetable mixture, then thoroughly rub vegetable mixture over the entire roast by hand.
If any of the mixture is left, spread it evenly over the top and a little on the sides of the roast.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours; change oven to 425° and bake until dark brown on top and meat is white in center, about 10 to 15 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: christmas wreath salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water. Chill until syrupy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on plate.
Garnish with holly. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix all but cukes.
Pour over cukes.
Refrigerate for 5 days, stirring once a day.
On day 5, put in containers and freeze. Will keep 3 to 4 months in refrigerator after thawing.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine juice from oranges and water in small saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Spoon in sherbet and stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add mandarin oranges.
Pour into 4-cup mold or into pretty glass bowl.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix in large bowl.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll in balls and dip in sugar.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: gaye's potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, water and salt in a large, covered pot.
Bring to a boil and add bouillon cubes.
Lower to a simmer and cook 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Mash with potato masher 2 or 3 times (leave some chunks of potatoes).
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring frequently.
Serve hot.
Makes about 7 cups.
Sprinkle top of your bowl with shredded cheese and/or crumbled bacon.

title: fruit fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine milk, egg and shortening.
Mix in dry ingredients just enough to combine.
Add apples and drop from a tablespoon into heated oil.
Cook until a golden brown on each side.
Sprinkle fruit fritters with powdered sugar.

title: grandma goyens raisin pie
directions: Combine in saucepan;
simmer
until thick.
Pour into 2 thin or 1 deep unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Do not peel (pare) cukes; slice thin.
Add onions, peppers and garlic.
Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice; mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cuke mixture.
Heat just to boiling.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: corn pone sticks
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into well greased corn stick pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Add eggs and flour alternately.
Then add flavoring.

title: low sodium cornbread
directions: Total liquid is 1 1/2 cups; includes milk and egg.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt and a small amount of water until well mixed.
Add egg yolks that have been beaten and cook until it begins to thicken.
Add the lemon juice and rind when thick enough. Add butter and pour into baked shell and cover with meringue and brown at 350°.

title: keith's no bake cookies
directions: Boil milk, sugar, cocoa and butter for one minute.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.
Cool.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown first 2 ingredients.
Add onion, salt, mustard, brown sugar, vinegar and ketchup.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves a lot!

title: banana split delight
directions: Prepare cake mix per directions.
Pour into 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken entree
directions: Arrange breasts in greased shallow pan (2-quart baking dish). Put cheese slices over chicken.
Mix soup with sherry.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
If you use a glass pan, bake at 325°.

title: danby's supersonic granola
directions: Mix oats, oil and sweetener together in a large bowl. Add coconut and nuts. Spread this mixture on a cookie sheet and bake for twenty minutes at 350° or 400°. Take out and stir around every five minutes. During the last five minutes, add wheat germ. Take out and let cool. Add as much dried fruit as you want, chopped apricots, raisins, peaches, cranberries, cherries, pineapple, dates, etc.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Put marshmallows in large bowl.
Cut up chunk pineapple into small pieces.
Add
a
little pineapple juice over marshmallows, which you have
saved.
Pour
light
cream over this. Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Next
day,
remove
and
whip mixture until creamy.
You may add a little milk to mixture if it is too dry.
Whip until creamy.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, salt, syrup and cocoa in pan.
Cook until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
(Never stir while boiling.)
Add vanilla.
Remove from stove; add butter.
Let cool to lukewarm. Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cut while still warm.

title: canned fruit coffee cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Add and thoroughly mix the flour, baking powder and vanilla. In a greased 9 x 13 pan, put half of the batter. Add either the apple, blueberry or cherry pie filling. Spread lightly over the batter. Spread the rest of the batter over the fruit. Sprinkle with topping make of 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then turn down to 325° for 35 minutes.

title: easy bacon onion tart
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Do not separate rolls.
Unroll dough in sheet and press perforations together to form a rectangle.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, except onions.
Mix well. Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onions.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cherries on the snow
directions: Mix wafers, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Line a 9 x 9-inch pan with crumb mixture.
Whip cream.
Fold in cream cheese and sugar; pour on top of crumb mixture.
Spread cherries on top.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, food coloring and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add and mix in buttermilk. Over top of cake batter, sprinkle vinegar and soda and fold in. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 (8-inch) layers or 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: refrigerator whole wheat rolls
directions: Add yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar to water.
Combine milk, 1/2 cup
sugar,
salt
and shortening; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture,
then egg.
Add to flour mixture.	Place dough mixture in greased bowl; cover and store in refrigerator.

title: potato dumplings for the sauerbraten
directions: Boil peeled potatoes for around 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Mash with a fork or grater.
Let air dry 30 minutes if very moist.
In a bowl, mix all of the ingredients.
Roll the potato mixture into 1 1/2-inch diameter balls and roll the balls in flour to lightly coat.
Boil salted water in a deep pot.
One at a time, drop half the balls into the water.
Boil potatoes 3 minutes after they rise to the top.
Remove potatoes with slotted spoon and drain on towels.
After the second batch, place potatoes in buttered dish in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate almond cake
directions: Combine all ingredients with spoon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: friendship casserole
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and
place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cover with 3/4 cup salted cashews or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: foolproof brownies
directions: Melt oleo in small pan; add cocoa.
In large bowl, cream sugar and eggs; add flour.
Add cocoa mixture and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Don't overcook.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and gelatin in 3 cups hot water.
Chop medium or coarsely the cranberries, apples and oranges with food processor or food chopper (peeling fruit).
Add nuts, sugar and pineapple and stir well.
Chill until firm.

title: marinated sweet and sour carrot salad
directions: Cook cleaned carrots in salted water until tender.
Set aside to cool and cut in rings.
Combine carrots, onion and pepper. Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, soup, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Pour the marinade over the vegetables.
Pour in covered dish and store in refrigerator.

title: aunt nettie's german chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in a 1-quart saucepan over low heat.
Set aside and let cool for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to the mixture.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Let cool and refrigerate.
To serve, cut into small wedges as this is quite rich, very much like fudge.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese scones
directions: Sift flour, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Rub in shortening. Stir in grated cheese. Make a well in the center of ingredients. Stir in egg. Stir until it forms a firm dough.
You may need 1 or 2 tablespoons milk to hold together.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil potato until tender.
Remove
peel and mash potato with about 1 teaspoon
milk.
Mix
powdered
sugar with mashed potato. It will become like
a
sticky dough.
Roll out dough mixture with rolling
pin,
about
1/2-inch thickness.
Spread peanut butter evenly on
dough mixture and roll tightly.
Wrap in wax paper and place in freezer for 1 hour.
When set, slice in 1/2-inch slices. The inside should look like a pinwheel.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Grease and flour cake pan.
Mix all the ingredients and stir until creamy smooth.
Bake at 350° until cake pulls away from sides of pan or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine white sugar, sour cream, white corn syrup, butter and salt in a heavy pan.
Bring very slowly to a boil, stirring until all sugar has melted.
Cover and boil without stirring for 3 minutes, so all sugar crystals are dissolved.
Uncover and boil on medium heat to 240°.
Remove from heat and let stand for 15 minutes.
Do not stir.
Then add vanilla and beat until mixture begins to lose its gloss.
Add peanut butter and continue beating (add nuts).
Entire baking time takes from 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 12 1/2-inch pan.
Crumble cookies fine.
Mix pudding by directions on box.
Put cookie crumbs in pan or glass dish.
Save some for topping.
Pour pudding mixture over crumbs. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add spaghetti sauce and water.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Pour into pie shell and top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut lard into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar. Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once.
Blend with a spoon just until flour is moistened.
This is an easy crust to handle and can be re-rolled without getting tough.
You can store in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: parmesan-ham twist with zesty dip
directions: Heat oven to 375° F.
Unroll dough, separate into 10 strips. Wrap 1 breadstick in spiral fashion around each ham stick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, tucking ends of dough under.
Brush with Parmesan spread over top of ham and breadstick.
Bake 375° for 10 to 14 minutes until golden brown.
In small bowl, microwave cheese, honey, mustard for 1 minute, stirring twice
Serve with ham twist.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; set aside 2 tablespoons juice.
In medium bowl, mix salmon, egg and onion; stir in flour.
Add baking powder to salmon juice.
Stir into salmon mixture.
Form into patties and fry until golden brown.
Serve with tartar sauce.
Quick, easy and nutritious.
Very good.

title: kroppkakor
directions: Cut salt pork into 1/2-inch cubes.
Fry gently with diced onion until nearly done. Combine potatoes, egg, salt and pepper and blend well.
Add 1/2 cup flour and mix.
Knead the rest of the flour into the dough on a board.
Make small balls and make a deep indentation in each.
Into the opening, put a portion of pork and onion mixture.
Close and roll in flour.
Drop into a kettle of boiling water and cook for 30 minutes.
Serve with cream sauce.

title: cool whip graveyard treat
directions: Mix 2 cups of cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press firmly on bottom of pan and refrigerate.

title: the best dressing
directions: Bake cornbread.
Saute onions and celery until transparent in butter.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until mixed thoroughly.
Press into 2 (15 x 9-inch) pans.
If you want, you can boil fresh chicken for chicken broth and save meat for giblet gravy.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Add green food color to add color.

title: peanut butter cakes
directions: Cream well the eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Add scalded milk and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately spread with peanut butter.
Cool in refrigerator until peanut butter is firm.
Melt chocolate and spread over peanut butter.

title: perfect roast chicken
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Thoroughly rinse chicken inside and out. Season with salt and pepper.
Place chicken on roasting pan with shallow sides, no higher than one inch, and place in oven.
Bake 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake 15 to 25 minutes more, or until the thigh meat registers 160° on a meat thermometer. Remove chicken from oven and let stand 10 to 20 minutes before carving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spray pan with Pam and pour mixture in pan. Cook 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Mix and put in bowl and refrigerate overnight, covered.
Next day, divide dough in parts.
Roll each piece like a pie crust and cut as a piece of pie. Roll each from large end to point after you butter the whole piece. Place on a pan and let raise 3 hours. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add apples and chopped nuts.
Pour into 9 1/2 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Serve plain or with sweetened whipped cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quiche
directions: Beat eggs well with milk.
Stir in cheese and ham (broccoli, if desired).
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Put together margarine (oleo), cocoa, Coca-Cola and heat until oleo is melted.
Do not boil.
Pour margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola mixture on top of flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk with baking soda.
Add eggs (well beaten).
Add vanilla.
Add marshmallows, well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana-pineapple yogurt smoothie
directions: Place yogurt in small bowl. Cover and freeze at least 6 hours or up to 2 days. Transfer frozen yogurt to blender. Add bananas, pineapple juice, ice cubes, and brown sugar. Blend until smooth. Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Combine caramel candies (each cut into 4 pieces) and flour. Add chopped apples, caramel topping and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into a frozen 9-inch pie crust and sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped peanuts.

title: sourdough cinnamon bread
directions: Mix and blend well, but do not overbeat.
For smaller loaves, use 3 pans.
For average large, use 2.
Grease pans with oleo or butter.
Sprinkle bottom and sides with sugar.
Pour into pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: curried lobster bisque
directions: In pan, saut all ingredients except for soup. Add soup and simmer on medium heat until thick. Serve over rice. Single serving.

title: spinach and eggs frittata
directions: Wash fresh spinach in cold water.
Steam or boil spinach until soft; drain and let cool slightly.
Chop spinach coarsely.
Set frying pan on stove with oil and garlic.
Turn heat on to medium setting.
Mix eggs and cooked spinach together.
Add cheese to taste (cheese helps to bind mixture and gives it a great flavor). Pour in spinach mixture.
Fry until set.
Slice frittata in triangles.
Turn and brown.
Serve with fresh salad and bread. Serves 4.

title: lazy tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to box.
Add tuna and mushroom soup; stir.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.
Can add 1 can sliced mushrooms.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for French fried onions. Put in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Heat in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put French fried onions on top for the last 10 minutes.

title: maple walnut muffins
directions: Mix liquid and dry ingredients thoroughly but separately, then combine and blend until smooth and well moistened.
(Mixture will be thick and lumpy, but will smooth out during baking.)
Bake at 450° 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: sweet italian sausage skillet
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Meanwhile, brown sausage in hot oil in large skillet over medium heat 5 minutes; drain.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, broth and beans.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Stir in pasta. Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: You will need 1 greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: pot roast with cornmeal dumplings
directions: Rub meat with salt and pepper; brown in hot fat in deep, heavy skillet.
Add tomato sauce, water and garlic.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Top with onion slices.
Combine brown sugar, paprika, mustard, catsup, lemon juice, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over meat.
Cover and cook until tender, about 1 hour. Remove meat before cooking dumplings.
To serve, place pot roast in center of large platter; arrange onion rings and dumplings around it.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken(cooked on gas grill)
directions: Beat egg very well, then add each ingredient and beat well after each one.
Marinate chicken in mixture at least 3 or 4 hours.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Add melted margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk to dry cake mix.
Press 1/2 of the cake mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.

title: caramel crisp bars
directions: Microwave 1/4 cup semisweet or milk chocolate chips and 2 teaspoons shortening in small microwavable bowl uncovered on High 45 seconds or until mixture can be stirred smooth.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well, put in casserole dish and bake for 25 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking pan with cooking oil.
Wash squash, cut off ends and cut longways (not in circles),* thickness is according to desired taste.
Coat squash with cornmeal and place in baking dish.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes or until brown.

title: decorating cake icing
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add powdered sugar and water alternately.
Mix well.
Add flavoring.
Mix well.
Add food coloring, if desired. (Paste food coloring works the best.)
If the humidity is high, you may have to add a little more powdered sugar or icing will be too watery.

title: pork casserole
directions: Brown pork in roaster.
Add mushroom soup and simmer.
Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Add to meat mixture.
Add pepper, pimento, corn, mushrooms and diced cheese; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix soups, beans and tomatoes together and heat while browning meat.
Put layer of Doritos, then a layer of canned mixture, a layer of cheese and meat in casserole. Repeat layers, making sure of hamburger being on top always.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles up.
Makes large amount.
Use 2 baking dishes or cut recipe in half.

title: cheesy-corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Saute onion and butter.
Mix eggs and milk.
Add corn and muffin mix; mix well.
Spread cornbread batter into dish.
Spoon onion over top, then spread sour cream over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes.
(Better the next day.)

title: seedless blackberry dumplings
directions: *If using flour, add 2 teaspoons baking powder and 1/2 cup butter or oil.

title: mom spano's white cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan. Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, into butter mixture.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder in separate bowl.
Beat in with electric beater 1/3 flour mixture and then 1/3 milk into butter mixture until all ingredients are used. Add vanilla and lemon.
Beat until creamy.
Bake 1 1/2 hours. Cool at room temperature before turning out of pan.

title: spanish rice and beans
directions: Heat oil in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion; cook, covered, 6 minutes or until softened, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chili powder and oregano; cook 1 minute.
Stir in rice, water, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a simmer.
Scatter peppers on top. Cook, covered, 10 minutes.
Stir in beans.
Makes 4 servings at 69 cents each.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine and sift sugar, flour, cocoa and salt. Mix well.
Gradually stir in milk.	Cook in double boiler over boiling water, stirring constantly until mixture begins to thicken. Put on top and cook for 15 minutes.
Remove top and stir small amount of hot mixture into yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes more, stirring constantly.	Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into baked pastry shell.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 3 hours before serving.

title: tri-color mochi
directions: Place dry ingredients in a bowl.
Slowly add liquids to the dry ingredients.

title: bottled zucchini bread
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Use wide-mouthed, tapered jars. Sterilize and grease jars.
Fill slightly more than half with batter. Set jars on cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes. Wipe rim very thoroughly with clean cloth.
Have lids hot and put on jars immediately.
Should seal within 1 or 2 minutes.
Makes 11 pints.
Stores well for 2 to 3 years.

title: quick cottage dip
directions: Combine onion, salt and cheese.
Beat well with electric mixer.
Chill several hours.
Stir in pimiento or parsley.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450.
Grease 9 inch square pan.
Beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat the egg whites stiff.
Add the sugar and cream of tartar; beat until stiff.
Add the crushed crackers and walnuts.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pizza
directions: Mix all in bowl and let rise in warm place for 1 hour.

title: divinity
directions: Mix ingredients and cook, stirring constantly until mixture forms a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Add mixture to 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup pecans, if desired.
Stir until almost cool.
Drop by the spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: chicken pot pie(one dish meal)
directions: Boil chicken until tender and done.
Save 2 cups of broth. Pull meat from bones and cut up fine.
Put meat and broth into casserole dish.
Mix in salt, pepper and soup.
Stir well.
Drain Veg-All and add to mixture.
Preheat oven to 425°.

title: scottish shortbread #1(really cookies)
directions: Cream the butter well.
Knead the butter, powdered sugar and flour together until well mixed.
Line a 9 x 9-inch pan with waxed paper. Spread well kneaded dough evenly in pan.
Prick with fork over the dough. Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until slightly tan color. Cut while still warm in pan in individual squares. Cool to remove carefully.
Put in an airtight container. Flavor improves with keeping.

title: carrot ring
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine all ingredients including egg yolks.
Pour into a buttered ring mold.
Set mold in pan of hot water.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Unmold and fill center with green peas or vegetable of your choice.

title: kentucky bluegrass fudge pie
directions: Grease an 8 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt on wax paper.
Spread nuts in a shallow pan. Toast in oven at 350°, stirring often for 10 minutes.
Cool; reserve.

title: spiced pineapple sparkle
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar; let cool.
Pour mixture through a large wire-mesh strainer into a punch bowl, discarding spices; stir in juices and lemon-lime beverage.
Garnish, if desired.
Yields 12 cups.

title: honey-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and honey, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in sour cream, blending well.

title: handy meat pies
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, brown the beef and sausage; drain.
Add onions and garlic; cook until tender.
Add parsley, water, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper; mix well.
Heat through.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
On a floured surface, pat 10 biscuits into 4-inch circles.
Top each with about 1/3 cup of the meat mixture.
Pat remaining biscuits into 5-inch circles and place over filling; seal edges with water.
Press edges together with a fork dipped in flour; pierce the top.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown and filling is hot.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook until tender the onion and ham, then add broccoli and cauliflower, cheese and half and half.
Heat through.

title: camp out mix
directions: In 2-gallon storage bag, combine cereal mixture.
Pour oil over mixture.
Close bag and gently toss until well coated.
Add dressing mix until well coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: cinnamon orange butter
directions: Cream together butter, grated peel of 1 orange, orange juice concentrate, brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Boil water.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick and clear.
Cool.
Add strawberry jello and allow to finish cooling. Pour over fresh strawberries in a baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Stir in water. Cook in microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes halfway through the cooking time.
Stir well.
When finished cooking, blend in oleo. Cook in microwave on High for 30 seconds more.
Blend in vanilla thoroughly.
Serve.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to directions.
Mix together and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer mushrooms and ham; mix in soup, mayonnaise, mustard, curry and Cheddar cheese; pour this mixture over all.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Melt together butter
or margarine and chocolate chips. In large bowl, combine
flour	and Eagle Brand.
Add chocolate mixture, vanilla and nuts.	Drop
on
greased
cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake at 350°
for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake; they are soft when done.
Makes 11 dozen.

title: oat pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix egg, yogurt and oil.
Combine and griddle as usual.

title: bavarian crown dessert
directions: Add sugar to Jell-O prepared in usual way except leave out 1 cup of water.
Use 3 cups for 2 packages.
While Jell-O is still warm, add strawberries, cut fine.
Let stand until it begins to thicken.
Break angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Place in a tube pan.
Pour part of Jell-O mixture and another layer until all mixture is used.
Let stand until congealed or overnight in refrigerator.
Remove from pan or mold and ice with whipped cream.

title: nut bar
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then add flour and beat as lightly as possible to mix well.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Grease 10 x 18-inch pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan and cook in preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Take out of oven and place on a wet dish towel and let cool completely.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: cream cheese puffs
directions: Mix together; dough will be sticky.
Roll to desired thickness, 1/8-inch.
Cut out 3-inch rounds or squares.

title: garlic green salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the mayonnaise, sour cream, garlic, salt, and pepper. Boil or steam broccoli for 5 to 6 minutes. Frozen broccoli 3 to 4 minutes. Just until crisp tender. Plunge the broccoli into a bowl of cold water to stop the cooking and to retain its bright green color. Drain well. Add broccoli to mayonnaise/ sour cream mixture. Refrigerate until chilled. Garnish with lemon or lime rind.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Slice hot dogs lengthwise, not cutting all the way through. Slice each piece of cheese into 5 strips and place one strip in each slit in the hot dogs.
Stretch and flatten rolls enough to wrap around the hot dog.
Place, cheese side up, on cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. When done, pour glaze over cake.

title: gourmet tossed green salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Wash cauliflower; remove green stalks and separate into tiny flowerets.
Cut onion in paper-thin rings.
Toss gently with green pepper, pimiento, mushrooms, cheese and garlic.
Chill about 1 hour.
Toss and serve immediately with low calorie French dressing.

title: cranberry dainties
directions: Cook cranberries and water until skins pop.
Remove from stove. Add liquid sweetener.
Beat until smooth.
Then return to heat and bring just to boiling point.
Add gelatin dessert and stir until dissolved.
Pour into an oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in 1-inch squares and roll in coconut.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions (two 9-inch layers). Mix sugar, vanilla and sour cream and let stand in refrigerator while cake is baking.
Cool cake; slice layers in half.
Pour sour cream mixture, coconut, nuts and cherries alternately on each layer.
Store in refrigerator.
Cake is best made a day before serving.

title: chocolate layer bars
directions: Cream margarine, white sugar and eggs together.
Add cocoa, flour and vanilla.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with 1/2 bag of miniature marshmallows.
Put back in oven for 3 minutes.
Let cool.

title: frozen delight
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and freeze until solid.
To serve, remove from freezer a little ahead of time.
When ready to serve, cut into squares.

title: butter mints
directions: Mix together.
Roll
out
less	than 1/4-inch thick and cut. Let dry several hours.
Use any color food coloring.

title: pineapple-pudding salad
directions: Whip cream until fluffy.
Add undrained crushed pineapple. Add instant pudding, powder only.
Mix through.
Chill for at least 4 hours.
Serve.

title: creamy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the hot water.
Cool and chill slightly.
Break up cranberry sauce with a fork and add to gelatin with the celery and nuts.
Fold in cream cheese.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: fig preserves with lemon
directions: Wash figs and remove stems; do not peel.
Place in saucepan; add water.
Sprinkle sugar on top and bring to a simmer.
Stir to distribute and help sugar to melt.
Wash lemon; slice into very thin cross-sections.
Discard seeds.
Cut slices in half and blanch in boiling water 1 minute; drain and add to figs.
Cook until figs are tender, stirring frequently.
When syrup thickens and darkens, remove from heat.
Allow to cool.
Store in jars and refrigerate.

title: quick ukrainian potato soup
directions: Boil 3 quarts water with tablespoon of salt.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon dough into boiling water; cook for 10 minutes.
Add diced potatoes; cook until they are soft.
Fry onions in butter until golden brown; add to soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes more and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Add ingredients as listed.
Cream sugar, Crisco and butter until fluffy.
Add flavoring and then flour.
Beat well after addition of each egg.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° in a preheated oven for one hour and 15 minutes.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven brown roast.
Add soup mix blended with 2 cups of water.
Simmer, covered, turning occasionally, 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Blend remaining water with flour.
Stir into gravy. Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring constantly until thickened about 5 minutes.

title: whole wheat carrot banana bread
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat margarine for 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flours, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients and banana alternately to batter mixture, beating after each addition.
Fold in carrots.
Pour into 2 greased 7 1/2 x 3 3/4 x 2-inch loaf pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: devil's food cookies
directions: Put buttermilk, chocolate and brown sugar in a small, heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon, until melted and smooth.
Remove pan from heat and stir in vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Position rack in center of oven; preheat to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 to 3 cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, and using an electric mixer set on medium speed, cream butter and granulated sugar until light and smooth.
Beat in egg until fluffy.
Beat in cooled chocolate mixture until blended.
In a small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add in 1/3's to chocolate mixture, blending with a rubber spatula after each addition.
Stir in sprinkles.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of dough onto greased cookie sheets, spacing about 2 inches apart.
Bake one sheet at a time for 8 to 10 minutes, or until cookies feel firm.
Remove sheet to wire rack and cool 2 minutes.
Using a metal spatula, slice cookies onto wire racks and cool completely.
Store cookies in an airtight container.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Stir in onion, egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pudding cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, milk and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Stir together 1 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup cocoa, 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and hot water. Carefully spoon over batter in pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail pie meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and salt and cook thick and clear. Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Continue beating while slowly pouring cooked mixture over.
Continue beating 5 minutes. Cover cooled filling in pie shell with meringue, sealing edges to crust.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes until golden brown.

title: cheese squares
directions: *Kaukauna, Merkt's or whatever brand you prefer.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Crisp-fry bacon and remove from skillet.
Add next 4 ingredients to bacon grease and fry until tender.
In a large pan combine and heat chicken broth, corn and parsley.
Add the bacon and vegetables to this.
In the skillet combine and blend oil, flour and milk and stir in some of the soup liquid.
Stir to thicken and pour back into soup.
Heat to scald but do not boil.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat or in a double broiler over water; stir constantly until thick. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Pour into pie crust.

title: french onion soup
directions: Place finely sliced onions in pan together with butter; stir and cook over low heat until onions are golden brown.
Add flour; continue to stir until flour is blended with butter and onions. Continue to cook about 3 minutes, then gradually stir in beef stock, blending with the rest.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover the pan and cook for 20 minutes.
When ready to serve, pour into bowls and top with slices of French bread, sauteed in butter.
Sprinkle with grated Gruyere cheese and place in a hot oven or under a broiler to brown cheese.
Serves 4.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill.
Very good on vegetables and chips.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refill quart jar. Refrigerate.
Will keep months in refrigerator.

title: garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Pat dry.
Saute potatoes and garlic in olive oil.
Add rosemary.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add egg, sugar and dates.
Cook for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove.
Add cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Form into 2 long rolls on wax paper that has powdered sugar sprinkled on it.
After they have cooled a little, press well so they will hold together.
Finish cooling in refrigerator, then slice.

title: hot dog wraps
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Mix molasses, pepper and dry mustard; pour over beans, liquid and onion.
Cover and bake at 300° for 45 minutes and then remove cover and continue baking until most of liquid is absorbed, approximately 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey manicotti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook manicotti in boiling water about 18 minutes or until tender but still firm.
Drain and rinse well.
In a large skillet, saute onion in a little margarine for 1 minute. Add turkey to onions and cook until no longer pink.
In another pot, heat sauce.
Add all the spices, the bay leaf and mushrooms. Heat through.
Stir in turkey and onions.
Mix together egg, Ricotta, Mozzarella, parsley and Parmesan in a separate bowl. Stuff cheese mixture into shells.
Spoon 1/3 of the sauce mixture into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place shells on top. Spoon the remaining sauce over the shells, covering them up. Bake, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until very soft.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk. Add remaining milk, sugar, vanilla and pudding mix; beat as directed on the pudding package for pie filling.
Pour into crust; chill for several hours or overnight.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs by placing in cold water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover with a tight fitting lid; let stand 15 minutes.
Turn heat off.
Cool eggs by running cool water over them.
Peel eggs.
Slice in halves lengthwise.
Remove yolks from each egg.
Place the yolks in a bowl and mash.
Add the other ingredients.
Mix, making sure it is not lumpy.
Spoon mixture into the whites of the eggs.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: red bean gumbo
directions: In a 4-qt pot, heat oil and stir in flour to make a small roux. Add onion and garlic.
Saute in roux for 5 minutes.
Cream red beans and add to mixture along with 6 cups water to thin your gumbo.
Bring to a boil once again and lower heat to cook for 1/2 hour.
Add salt to taste.
With gumbo on simmer, break 1 egg at a time and drop slowly into gumbo.
Do not stir for at least 20 minutes, allowing eggs to cook whole.

title: peanut butter cookie
directions: Mix butter and sugar, then add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and soda sifted and mix.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; mix well. Form in balls, flatten and press with fork tines.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked cheese potato slices
directions: Combine soup, pepper and paprika; then place potatoes in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with soup mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Uncover, and bake for 5 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour slowly.
Add flavoring.
Pour into large greased and floured tube cake pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open door while baking.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Beat eggs until foamy.

Stir together eggs and butter; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Place foil baking cups in muffin pans, and coat with cooking spray; spoon batter into cups, filling two-thirds full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Remove from pans immediately, and cool on wire racks.
Yield: 9 muffins.

title: easter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water with the 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Add lukewarm milk and 1/2 of flour; mixture will be wet. Place flour mixture in greased bowl and let rise about 2 minutes. Add eggs, margarine, sugar, salt and remainder of flour.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise until double in size, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cheese biscuitsspringfield, missouri
directions: Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon and set aside.

title: family favorite potato salad
directions: While potatoes are still warm, use a sharp knife and finely cut about 1/4 of the potatoes against the side of bowl. Fluff into the rest of small cubed potatoes. Add remaining ingredients in order.
Mix with hand gently.
Place in serving bowl and chill for 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: flaming flamingos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning, cumin and peppers along with 1 1/2 cups water.
Simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until water cooks down.
(If you don't like things hot, do not use jalapeno peppers or crushed red peppers.)

title: nona's lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter (not melt).
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Cook in slow oven at 325° to 350°.
This makes 2 large layers or 3 small layers.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn hot and crisp in slow oven.
Combine sugar, water, syrup, vinegar and vanilla.
Cook to hard-ball stage (250°).
Pour slowly over popcorn.
Mix well to coat every kernel. Use butter on hands to press into balls.
Makes about 20 balls.

title: ham-potato casserole
directions: In large saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter and stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cheese. Cook, stirring until cheese melts.
Gently stir in ham and potatoes and arrange in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and cream of wheat dumplings
directions: Boil chicken, cool and debone.
To make dumplings, mix margarine and water; bring to a boil.
Mix cream of wheat and flour; add to boiling water and margarine.
Cook until mixture forms a ball. Cool to warm.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each until mixed and smooth.
Drop by heaping teaspoons into boiling chicken broth.
Dip teaspoon into broth each time before adding dumpling to enable it to slide off spoon.
Simmer until dumplings rise to top of broth or cut a dumpling to see if done.
Serve with chicken.

title: date cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Cream butter and cheese together.
Blend in flour and salt. Chill several hours.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness on board sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Cut in 1 x 3-inch strips. Put a date in center of each strip and roll up.
Put folded side down on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: freezer ice pack for booboos
directions: Mix alcohol and water.
Pour in large Ziploc bag, pressing out excess air.
Store in freezer and use when needed.
Bag will form to whatever area it is applied to when done.
Simply place back in freezer.

title: etta's corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add shortening, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour in greased pan (cast-iron frypan is good).
Bake at 425° about 45 minutes, until brown.
Remove from oven and rub margarine over top until melted into bread.

title: harvard carrots
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add carrots and let stand over low heat 5 to 10 minutes.
Add butter.
Serves 6.

title: hot fudge cake pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in shortening and milk. Add nuts and vanilla. Spread in greased pan.
Top with 3 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup brown sugar, mixed together.
Pour 1 1/2 cups hot water over entire batter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve as is with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Mix melted oleo and vanilla wafers and pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish for crust.
Layer sliced bananas on crust.
Mix condensed milk and lemon juice and pour on top of bananas.
Next, put layer of drained pineapple, then sprinkle coconut on top. Spread Cool Whip over top, covering to the edges.
Sprinkle pecans and cherries to decorate.
Put in refrigerator immediately.

title: english pea salad(club member: john waters)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serves 6.

title: eclairs
directions: Form eclairs 1 inch apart and 3 to 4 inches long.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut eclairs in half and fill with custard or vanilla pudding.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme.
Add Cool Whip.
Serve with fruit.

title: pork in gorgonzola
directions: Careful with salt as cheese already has salt.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and form into a loaf.
Put into a loaf pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° uncovered for about 1 hour.
Let set a few minutes before slicing.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix at low speed until all ingredients are well blended and then on high speed until mixture is smooth.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer pans at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Frost with Seven Minute or Buttercream Icing.

title: frozen treat
directions: Fill cups about 2/3 full with fruit.
Put into freezer until frozen.
Serve instead of popsicles to be eaten with spoon.
This recipe is so easy kids can make it themselves.

title: chocolate coconut clusters(tastes like mound bars)
directions: Melt chocolate slowly over boiling water or in microwave 45 seconds, until soft.
Add coconut and coat evenly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Chill.

title: february favorite pie
directions: Line a 9-inch plate with pie crust. Pour in cherry pie filling. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients and carefully pour over half baked pie. Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.

title: tomato cheese pie
directions: Pre-bake pie crust 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Prick bottom and sides with a fork to prevent shrinking.
Combine first 6 ingredients and spoon into crust.
Slice tomatoes into wedges and arrange over the filling in a tightly overlapping circular pattern.
Sprinkle on the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: spicy santa fe casserole
directions: Heat oil in electric skillet.
Place chicken pieces in hot oil.
Sprinkle with paprika, pepper, salt, cumin, chili powder and garlic powder.
Saute over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add onions, bell pepper and fresh garlic.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Mix canned tomatoes and green chiles with chicken broth.
Add to skillet and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; return to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low simmer.
Do not stir.
Cook, covered, until the rice is just done (you do not want the rice totally dry).
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Do not stir. Turn heat off and replace lid to melt.
Serve with Southern Style Salad Biscuit Muffins (recipe follows).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce of first five ingredients (shredded cheese may be added to sauce).
Place half of the potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half the onion and then half the sauce. Repeat the layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Mix peanut butter and butter.
Stir until smooth.
Mix powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs together.
Pour over peanut butter.
Mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt oleo and butterscotch chips together.
Pour over mixture in pan and spread.
Refrigerate several hours.
Cut and serve.

title: mom's deviled eggs
directions: Place eggs in saucepan.
Cover eggs with water.
Bring to rolling boil.
When water boils, place cover on saucepan and turn off heat. Leave for 15 minutes, then drain and rinse eggs with cold water.
Crack eggs and remove outer shells*.
Cut eggs in half.
Put yolks in bowl.
Mix into yolks, deviled ham, mayonnaise, onion and salt and pepper.
Mix well until smooth. Fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Arrange on plate.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Wash bulgur, place in large bowl and cover with hot water; let stand for 20 minutes.
Drain thoroughly and squeeze dry with hands.

title: drop yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar and oil.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 full. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Store in refrigerator in a covered container for up to one week and use as needed.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with 2 cups corn flakes or Ritz crackers (crushed) and 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: divinity
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, place the sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Then cook without stirring to 252° on candy thermometer or hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and pour into stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating until mixture loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop quickly from tip of spoon onto waxed paper or spread in greased pan.
Cut into squares when cool. Makes 18 to 24 pieces.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Brown onion; add corned beef, water, brown sugar and catsup; simmer until all is cooked and stirred together.
Add the cornstarch; mix well and let cool.
Place on bread, toast or browned buns.

title: spinach spread
directions: Thaw spinach; drain thoroughly, squeezing out extra liquid. Wash parsley; pat dry on paper.
In food processor, chop parsley, using steel blade.
Add spinach and remaining ingredients; pulse until combined.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Serve with thin wheat crackers, buttery crackers or celery and cheese sticks.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: brownies
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into 8 x 8 x 2 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pokey beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 6 hours.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat; stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition; add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture, coconut and peanuts to ingredients in saucepan.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cut bars while warm.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Remove from pan when almost cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Zucchini, onions and pepper should be finely chopped.
If desired, hot red pepper can be used in place of red sweet pepper or pimento.
Mix with salt; let stand overnight.
In the morning, wash in cold water and drain.
In large saucepan, combine vinegar, sugar, mustard, nutmeg, cornstarch, turmeric, celery seed and pepper.
Cook for 30 minutes, then add vegetable mixture and cook for 20 minutes.
Process and seal in hot jars.
Yields 7 pints.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet and roll thin, closing perforations.
Bake at 375°.
Watch closely and let cool.

title: tuna flake loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cereal and milk in a bowl; let stand 10 minutes, then add tuna, onion, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in eggs.
Pour into well-greased, aluminum foil lined 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve with cheese or mustard sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blue cheese vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and place in covered container.
Refrigerate 1 hour or so or overnight.

title: miracle salmon loaf
directions: Mix together all but salmon and bread crumbs.
Mix well, then add the salmon and bread crumbs.
Bake in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate mint fudge
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 8 x 8-inch or 7 x 10-inch pan. Microwave all ingredients on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until chips melt.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut and serve.

title: mclees' no-bake cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a heavy pan to "soft ball" stage. Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper; let cool.

title: zucchini and dill soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot over medium high heat.
Add next 4 ingredients and saute until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add broth and bring soup to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Dip tortillas in sauce. Layer tortillas and all other ingredients.
Repeat and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown beef, drain fat and stir in water and all ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes. Season to taste.
If too thick, add water.
Stir in cubed cheese until melted.
Serves 6.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Put 1/2 pound
hamburger
on bottom of a 2 quart casserole. Add
onions, potatoes, rice and celery.
Pat other half of hamburger
on
top.
Then
pour
undrained	beans
on
top. Spread tomato soup
over all.
Add 3 or 4 slices bacon.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: mexican shrimp appetizer(aperitivo de camaron ala mexicana)
directions: Marinate shrimp for 2 hours in oil, vinegar, lemon juice, Tabasco and onions.
Add tomatoes, olives, parsley, salt and oregano.
Marinate, stirring gently 3 or 4 times, for 2 to 3 hours (or longer).
When ready to serve, add avocado and place semi-drained in a lettuce lined glass bowl or for individual servings, serve in icers, large sea shells (for cooking and serving) or in individual ramekins.
Makes 6 appetizer servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Add baking soda to applesauce and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour and dry ingredients and add to cream mixture. Add raisins and applesauce mixture.
Turn into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chocolate italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well each time.
Sift together flour, baking soda and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans. Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then turn out on racks to cool completely.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° until done, almost 20 to 30 minutes.
Has the same texture as brownies.

title: potato-broccoli bake
directions: Place potatoes in greased 7 x 10-inch baking dish.
Combine butter, salt, pepper and paprika.
