Brush potatoes with butter mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and arrange broccoli over potatoes.
Pour Cheese Sauce over broccoli.
Cover and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in top of a large double boiler. Beat at low speed with an electric mixer 30 seconds or just until blended.
Place over boiling water; beat constantly at high speed 7 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Yield:
4 1/2 cups.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme; chill.
Serve with fresh fruit pound cake, vanilla wafers, etc.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all in a mixer.
Place in pie shell and put in freezer. Use an 8-inch graham cracker pie shell.

title: blackberry pudding tarts
directions: Bake tart shells according to package directions; cool completely.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place beef on bottom of casserole dish.
Wrap 1 strip bacon around each breast.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: little cheddar loaves
directions: Combine beef, oatmeal, salt, cheese, onion, egg and milk in large bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 6 small loaves.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour over top of loaves.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Add chopped eggs, carrots, celery, onion and pickles to peas. Add mustard, mayonnaise and salt to taste.
Mix carefully, so as to not mash peas.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle yeast over water in a large bowl.
Stir it.
Stir in sugar, 1 cup flour and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg, shortening and remainder of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Scrape bowl down and cover.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Stir down.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin pan cups.
Cover and let rise for 15 minutes.
Bake about 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Brush with butter.
Cool on rack.
Wrap in foil to freeze up to 4 months.
Reheat in foil at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: pasta bella
directions: In large skillet stir-fry broccoli and carrots in margarine 3 minutes.
Add squash and asparagus; stir-fry until crisp-tender. Reduce heat to medium.
Add Velveeta, half and half and oregano. Stir until cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate nut toffee
directions: Spread pecans on bottom of pan.
Combine butter and brown sugar; boil for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour immediately over nuts.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of toffee.
Place breadboard on top to keep heat in.
When softened, spread evenly. When cool, break into pieces.

title: bride's pink punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine drink mix and cold water.
Mix in sugar and stir well.
Add pineapple juice and gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate.
Add lemon-lime beverage and sherbet before serving.
Yield:
Approximately 35 servings.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly all together (except nuts) and shape into a ball. Roll in crushed walnuts. Chill about 4 hours or overnight. Serve with snack crackers.

title: butter frosting
directions: Add food coloring or a little water if you want white frosting.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Spray Pam on a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Quarter tortilla shells.
Mix chicken with soup, sour cream and chiles and half of cheese.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place some chicken mixture on bottom of pan.
Place 1 layer of tortilla shells; repeat layers.
Top with half of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Remove bone from salmon.
Combine salmon, onion, egg and bread slices.
Mix well.
Shape croquettes; roll in flour and fry in a heavy frying pan on medium heat.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with French fries, salad and corn bread.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine Sugar, Flour and salt in a medium bowl.
Add butter, mix well.
Add Eggs to bowl and beat until blended.
Add Vinegar, Flavorings and Coconut to bowl and mix well.
Pour filling into Pie Shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes, or until Pie is set. Shield Pie with foil after baking for 25 minutes.

title: *goodie bars
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Press into a lightly greased sheet cake pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips, and put in a casserole dish, then sprinkle potato chips over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut milk cake
directions: Mix as given.
Add sour cream last; mix well.
Bake in 3 round pans or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 450° (hot).
Combine ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Pile lightly in seashells or individual baking dishes.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: elbow macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Cook elbow macaroni until tender.
Blend tomatoes in blender until all chopped.
Combine all ingredients (except Cheddar cheese) until well mixed.
Top with Cheddar cheese and put in ungreased casserole dish with lid.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until Cheddar cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: bud's ho cake(in memory of husband emory bryant)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in an omelet pan over low heat.
When brown, turn over and brown other side.
Serve hot or cold.
Very good with fresh sweetened strawberries or sliced peaches with whip cream.
Yum Yum!

title: quaker's best oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; add to margarine mixture, mixing well. Stir in oats.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mint chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars in microwave or double boiler.
Cool. Stir in Cool Whip. Spread evenly in crust.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving (or freeze for 30 minutes).
Garnish as desired.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except breadcrumbs, cheese and butter. Turn into casseroles and top with crumbs and cheese; dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add stuffing; put half of mixture into the bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over stuffing; top with remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Baste on chicken on the grill until chicken is done.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple.
Chill to soft consistency.
Add nuts and cranberry sauce.

title: hot chicken and cheese canapes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread on crackers or toast squares. Broil 4 inches from heat until cheese melts.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: cereal brittle
directions: Mix cereal and nuts in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bring corn syrup, margarine and brown sugar to a boil and cook for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over cereal and nuts; mix well.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour, mixing every 20 minutes.
Place on a cookie sheet and let cool completely.
Break into pieces when cool and store in a tin or plastic bag.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: easy taco meat
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Freezes well for once-a-month cooking plan.

title: millionaire's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Chill.

title: slaw
directions: Shred cabbage very thin.
Do not chop.
Place in bowl.
Slice onion very thin.
(Do not chop.)
Slice pepper very thin.
Mix with cabbage.
Sprinkle sugar over mixture.
(Do not stir.)
Pour vinegar and oil over the mixture.
(Do not stir.)
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator.
Let set at least 1 hour.

title: pasta salad(quick and easy)
directions: Boil and drain noodles.
Rinse with cold tap water to stop cooking process and prevent sticking.
Slice and cube all ingredients.
Mix everything (except noodles) and add both dressings, Cajun seasoning and grated cheese.
Mix well.
Add noodles and mix well again.
Chill in fridge.
Serve cold.
Will keep for several days.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, flour and jello.
Add oil, warm water and berries.
Add eggs and mix.
Pour into greased and floured iron skillet (No. 2).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Follow Solomon's prescription for a good boy in Proverbs 23:14 and bake.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut avocado in half, remove seed, take from shell and place in blender.
Put in all other ingredients.
(Tomato and onion may need to be cut up some.)
Process on high speed until smooth.

title: spicy baked shrimp(makes 4 servings)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add shrimp and toss to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix well. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beef or chicken stir-fry
directions: In a skillet or wok over high heat, in 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry beef or chicken until browned.
Remove to bowl and toss with soy sauce.
Add a little more (1 tablespoon) oil to skillet. Stir-fry vegetables, onion and garlic until vegetables are tender-crisp.
In a cup combine broth and cornstarch.
Add to skillet with beef.
Cook mixture until thickened, stirring often. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Make ground meat into meatballs.
Cook in sauce.
Mix with cooked spinach.
Combine Ricotta cheese, salt, pepper, Mozzarella cheese, eggs and chopped parsley.
Stuff cooked shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake with spaghetti sauce, sprinkled with Parmesan cheese, for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugar until light and fluffy. Continue creaming; add eggs slowly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Bake at 400° on a greased baking sheet for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients and cook in an unbaked pie shell at 375° until done (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).

title: jello  salad
directions: Mix all together and put into large casserole dish. Refrigerate until set. When set spread cool whip on top.

title: chicken cacciatore(serves 8)
directions: Saute chicken in hot salad oil until golden brown.
Add onions, green peppers and garlic and brown lightly.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, wine, salt, pepper, ginger, allspice, bay leaves, thyme and cayenne pepper.
Simmer uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Arrange chicken on heated platter and pour sauce from skillet over chicken.
Serve with buttered garlic French bread and tossed green salad.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients together in shallow baking pan. Then mix coconut, nuts, flour and remaining butter.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° until coconut browns.

title: turkey broccoli casserole
directions: In a saucepan, mix broccoli, 1/2 soup, margarine and contents of vegetable packet from stuffing mix.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add stuffing crumbs and stir to moisten.
Spoon into a 9-inch square baking dish.
Arrange turkey on top.
Stir milk with rest of soup and pour over turkey. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken florentine supreme
directions: Lightly
grease
an
x
7-inch glass dish.	Combine chicken,
spinach,	Cheddar
cheese and onion; spoon into prepared dish.
Combine
remaining
ingredients;	blend
until smooth. Pour over chicken mixture.	Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes
or until
knife
inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: chicken - pork adobo
directions: Place the pork and chicken in a saucepan.
Add vinegar, garlic, pepper, soy sauce, bay leaf and water.
Cover and cook slowly until most of the broth has evaporated and only about 1/4 cup remains and meat is tender (2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours).
Remove liquid and set aside.
Brown pork and chicken in oil.
Pour in liquid and simmer a few minutes more.
Serve hot.
Good for six to ten people.

title: zucchini and tomato bake
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Add zucchini, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper. Pour into covered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake an additional 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: vegetable soup(lo-cal)
directions: Combine juice, pepper, oregano and salt in large kettle. Bring to boil.
Add 4 cups of the vegetables or your choice. Cover.
Lower heat and simmer until vegetables are cooked.

title: worcestershire chicken
directions: Skin chicken, then salt and pepper.
Melt oleo in oven.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Place in baking dish, cover and cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, turning once.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Fry hamburg and sausage; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat. Top each muffin half with sauce mixture.
Add cheese or any other topping you like.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat together the first six ingredients in a mixing bowl; mix well.
In a small bowl, sift together remaining ingredients; add this to pumpkin mixture.
Stir batter until it is just combined. Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon into 12 buttered muffin cups.
Fill each 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Use 2-quart saucepan.
Cook ham, beef or chicken until almost done.
Add celery, onions, stewed tomatoes, corn and sugar.
Steam about 15 minutes.
Drop whole okra on top of stew and bring to a boil (add a little water if necessary).
Turn flame low, cover and steam 10 minutes.
Serve with rice or as side dish.
Also can be served as stew by adding an extra pint of water before bringing to a boil.
As with all recipes, nothing brings out the taste like a little TLC while preparing and serving.

title: ponderosa ice cream
directions: Mix all together in freezer can real well and then fill freezer can with milk to line on can.
Turn on freezer or crank until done.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cheese and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Stir yeast in warm water; set aside.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture is like cornmeal.
Stir in the buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Blend well.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board. Knead until smooth.
Add flour if dough is sticky.
Put dough in bowl; let rise 30 minutes.
Roll dough out 2 inches thick; cut out biscuits.
Bake 1 inch apart.
Bake on a high rack in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Grease dish.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add sauce, beans and onion; simmer.
Grate and add half of the cheese.
Fry shells in oil.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons of meat on each shell.
Roll up and put in pan.
Pour rest of sauce over top of full pan.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: alice's hot curried fruit
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; add brown sugar, the reserved syrup and curry powder.
Simmer until sugar melts.
Place fruit in casserole; pour mixture over it.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pork steak and corn dressing
directions: Brown pork steak on both sides.
Remove from pan and season with salt and pepper.
In the drippings add the bread cubes (or stuffing) and corn.
Sprinkle with sage and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Place stuffing in a 13 x 9-inch roasting pan.
Place pork steaks on top of stuffing.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until meat is done.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: impossible spinach pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and pour into 10-inch pie plate.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix soup, ground beef, potatoes and peas.
Put in a dish. Place grated cheese on top.
Cook 15 minutes at 350° in the oven. Then place onions on top and cook for 5 more minutes.

title: golden pork chop dish
directions: Mix rice, soup and water in baking dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour hot water over jello
in a medium bowl, stir until dissolved.	Add sugar,
stirring until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring gently.
Pour
mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chill overnight or until set.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, onion tops and 1 package beef (chopped).
Mix well.
Form into ball.
Roll in second package of beef (chopped).
Wrap in foil.
Chill overnight. Can be used at several parties, just remold and keep in Tupperware.
Serve with crackers.

title: open-faced omelet
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender but not brown.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook just until tomatoes are heated through.
Keep warm while preparing omelet. Mix eggs and water with fork.
Heat butter in 10-inch omelet pan or skillet until just hot enough to sizzle a drop of water.
Pour in egg mixture.
Mixture should set at edges at once.

title: zucchini-oatmeal muffins
directions: Grease 12 (3-inch) muffin cups.
Measure first 7 ingredients into large bowl and beat eggs slightly in medium bowl.
Stir in zucchini and oil (or yogurt).
Stir this all at once into flour mixture until moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin tins.
Bake approximately 25 minutes at 400° (makes 12 to 18).

title: quick rolls
directions: Scald milk, add sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in water and add to milk; add shortening and flour.
Knead well.
Place in greased bowl, cover and set in warm place to rise.
When dough is light, shape into rolls or round buns.
Bake in hot oven for about 20 minutes.

title: citrus salad(5 star salad)
directions: In a large bowl, combine fruit, sour cream, marshmallows and coconut.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours, if desired. Serve in lettuce lined bowl or salad plates.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: poulet de normandy
directions: Mix stuffing and butter-water mixture.
Set aside.
Combine onions, celery, mayonnaise and salt.
Mix well with bread mix.

title: wanda's way goulash
directions: Brown meat lightly and drain.
Add chopped onions and bell pepper.
Cook until onions are clear, about 5 minutes.
Add seasonings, Ro-Tel, water and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and cook until macaroni is tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cheese packet from macaroni and cook 5 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Drain off grease.
Set aside. In a large bowl mix milk and Velveeta cheese.
Put in the microwave until cheese is melted.
Fold in 2 cans Ro-Tel and the meat.
Stir all together.
Dip your tortilla, Doritos or whatever you like into this.

title: cornmeal dumplings
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt. Beat egg and stir into milk before blending in dry ingredients.
Stir in melted butter.
Drop by spoonfuls into 5 to 8 cups stock.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press into 9 x 13 cake pan.
Chill.
Whip powdered sugar, eggs and soft margarine, 15 minutes.
Spread over chilled graham cracker layer. Drain pineapple, save juice to coat bananas, optional.
Spread pineapple over sugar mixture.
Slice bananas into juice, keeps the bananas from turning brown.
Layer bananas over pineapple, remove the juice first.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Dot with cherries.
Dot with nuts.
Chill Well.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Stir in bananas.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Loaf pan should be greased.

title: preacher cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine butter, milk, sugar and cocoa. Heat to boiling and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let stand until cool and firm.

title: winter sports grog
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and heat gently.
Add cinnamon sticks and orange slices and heat 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pink cloud dessert
directions: Thoroughly crush berries with potato masher.
Combine crushed berries and remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at highest speed for about 10 minutes until mixture is thick and fluffy. Chill until serving time.
Top each serving with a whole berry. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Bring 2 cups of water, cherry gelatin and red hots to a boil until red hots melt.
Add 2 cups applesauce.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: asparagus and pea casserole(8 servings)
directions: Place layer of asparagus in bottom of casserole.
Put layer of peas on top of asparagus.
Cover with can of undiluted cream of mushroom soup.
Dot with oleo (you may not want to use the whole stick).
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: hello dolly pie
directions: Mix chocolate chips, flake coconut and pecan pieces.
Pour into pie shell.
Pour over this the can of condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: mrs. stephen's popcorn balls
directions: Bring to boil sugar, syrup, water, vinegar and cream of tartar.
Boil to crackly stage. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, except food coloring.
Stir well, then add food coloring.
Pour over popped corn.
Grease hands well with butter and form into balls.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add enough dressing to coat well. Chill overnight.
Serve cold.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir in cornmeal.
Beat eggs, milk and butter together.
Make well in dry ingredients and add liquid ingredients.
Fold only until blended. Bake in greased 9-inch pan at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mix; beat well.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put sugar and spices in percolator basket and perk.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all together and chill.
More sugar may be used if desired.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together flour, salt and baking powder.
In a large bowl, cream together butter, sugar and peanut butter.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add sifted ingredients alternating with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dietetic oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, Sugar Twin, vanilla and egg. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients:
flour, salt, soda, cinnamon.
Fold in until well mixed.
Add water.
Stir in rolled oats and raisins and nuts (Dough will be soft.)
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for about 12 minutes or until cookies are set.
Makes about 40 cookies.
Keeps better if refrigerated.

title: coconut-date balls
directions: Stir together dates, sugar, pecans and eggs in medium size saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, 8 minutes or until thickened and beginning to simmer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and cereal until combined.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: streusel topping
directions: Stir together sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle and bake dough.

title: carolina skillet cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and lightly flour cake pan or iron skillet (10-inch in diameter).
Cream shortening, gradually adding sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pan or skillet and top with Crumble Topping.
Make indentations in batter with your finger all the way to the bottom of pan, so the topping will bake into the cake.
Bake 35 minutes. If desired, drizzle with confectioners sugar icing.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cover zucchini, bell pepper and salt with water.
Let set 4 hours.
Gently rinse.
Bring to boil sugar, cider vinegar, cloves, turmeric, celery seed and both mustards.
Add drained zucchini mixture.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pack in hot, sterile jars and seal. Yields 10 to 12 half-pints.

title: broccoli crabmeat casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients except crumbs.
Put crumbs on top, ending with some butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Brown ground beef; remove fat.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until macaroni is cooked.

title: spicy liverwurst mix
directions: Mash liverwurst with fork.
Add peanut butter, blend well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve with toasted whole wheat bread.
Makes 1 2/3 cups sandwich spread.

title: pork chops and rice bake
directions: In a baking dish, mix soup, water, rice, salt and pepper. Place pork chops on rice mixture and add melted margarine. Cover and bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat shortening until fluffy.
Gradually add well beaten egg and beat well.
Add sugar.
Add flour and bananas alternately beating well after each addition.
Pour into a well-greased bread pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Combine pecans, fruit and 1 tablespoon flour in a small bowl; set aside.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter; gradually beat in 1 1/2 cups sugar until lightly fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Spoon 1/2 batter into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Spoon nuts and fruit over batter; sprinkle sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Spoon remaining batter.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl.
Fill 4 greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
May be frozen.

title: sugar-free cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is absorbed.
Mix remaining ingredients together and bake in 8 x 8-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in crock-pot; add sauce and garlic powder.
Let cook all day and serve with noodles and a salad.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and sugar. Add shortening and work in dry ingredients with blender until it looks like fine meal.
Add egg, mashed bananas, oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: In a bowl, combine the cake mix, eggs, and extract.
Add pie filling, mix well.
Spread into a greased 15 x 10
x 1 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 18-22 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter.
Cook and stir until sugar is dissolved and butter is melted.
Removed from the heat, stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Pour over warm cake, spread evenly. Cool completely before cutting.
Store in the refrigerator.
Yield:
32 servings.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Put macaroni in a baking dish.
Put the cheese in and mix through.
Add milk and mix.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until thick.
Serves 8.

title: baklawa
directions: Combine walnuts, sugar and flower water and mix well.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in punch bowl.
Float strawberries and sherbet scoops on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Season as desired. Brown in skillet.
Break bread into small pieces; soak in melted butter and set aside.
Mix cream of chicken soup and 3/4 cup mayonnaise in a bowl.
Layer chicken pieces in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add a layer of broccoli and a layer of mayonnaise mixture.
Top with shredded cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls on waxed paper. Chill; then enjoy.

title: pizza cups
directions: To cooked and drained sausage add pizza sauce, ketchup, onion and seasoning.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin pan, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons into each cup and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
(Freezes well.)

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry hamburger; heat enchilada sauce. Heat refried beans.
Dunk tortillas into sauce.
Spread refried beans, hamburger and cheese into center of tortilla; roll tortilla up.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat as many times as needed.
Put in preheated oven until top layers of cheese is melted (about 2 to 5 minutes).

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk; add breadcrumbs and butter.	Add sugar, salt and nuts to eggs, then slowly stir in hot milk mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish; set into pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.
May add 1/2 cup raisins if desired.

title: uncooked frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with electric mixer until of fluffy spreading consistency.
Frost cake.
Serve within a few hours or refrigerate.
Frosts one 8 or 9-inch square/round cake or a loaf cake.

title: quick rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar and margarine, let cool to tepid.
Add dissolved yeast, well-beaten egg yolks, flour and salt.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Grease hands with butter; pinch off rolls the size of a walnut.
Place on shallow greased pan, press down; let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes 48.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Put berries and sugar in a covered casserole; bake in a 350° oven
for
20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir well; add marmalade, nuts and ginger.
Store in refrigerator.

title: almond roca
directions: Melt butter and margarine.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add chopped almonds and stir until caramel color.
It will take a long time to change color.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Cool.
Cover one side with melted chocolate bits and ground almonds.
Cool.
May repeat on other side.
Cool.
Break in pieces and store in sealed container.

title: friendship cake
directions: Cream greetings and smiles thoroughly.
Add all handshakes, beaten separately and add love slowly.
Sift sympathy and hospitality and fold in carefully.
Bake in moderate warm heart. This serves an indefinite number and never becomes stale.

title: old time brunswick stew
directions: Cook pork and hen until done tender.
Grind meat and set aside.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in water to cover until soft and tender.
Drain and cut up.
Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in orange juice, baking powder, baking soda, salt and flour.
Stir in nuts and apricots.
Grease two bread pans and line with foil; grease foil.
Pour in batter.
Let sit 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Remove from pan, peel off foil and cool.

title: bean cheese dip
directions: Layer each, starting with refried beans and ending with cheese, in a large, flat casserole.
Heat in oven at 325° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve with corn chips.
Good for a crowd.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs; add oil. Mix with grated ingredients, then add Bisquick and spices.
Spread in an 11 x 7-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: nut bars
directions: Beat eggs.
Add brown sugar.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients. Add walnuts; do not chop walnuts.
Leave in large pieces.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: minted melon ball
directions: Combine sugar, water and mint leaves in a saucepan; stir well. Bring to boil over medium heat and boil for 2 minutes.
Discard mint leaves.
Add lemon juice to syrup mixture, stirring well. Chill thoroughly.
Combine melon balls in serving dish.
Pour syrup mixture over fruit and toss gently.
Garnish fruit with mint sprigs.
Makes 8 servings.

title: best coleslaw ever
directions: Shred the cabbage, add the green and red peppers.
Combine the vinegar, oil and seasonings and pour over cabbage.
Toss lightly. Serve immediately.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Spread on halves of English muffins. Freeze on cookie sheets.
Stack when frozen.
When ready to use, cut frozen halves into quarters.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until tops bubble.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Drain pineapple and add. Stir in bread cubes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: herbed brown rice and chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder and pepper.
Brown chicken for 10 minutes on medium heat;
remove from skillet.
Stir in thyme, peas, broth and rice.
Heat to boil. Return chicken to pan. Cover and cook on low heat until rice is done (30 minutes).
Or, bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken.
Stir cheese into rice mixture, fluff and serve.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar together until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Spread the crumbs on the bottom of the baked pie shell.

title: linda's amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, biscuit mix, eggs, margarine and vanilla in blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut after 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sonara chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix soups, chili, chili salsa, milk and onion.
Tear tortillas into small pieces and put aside.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole (shallow), layer the chicken, then half of the tortillas and half of the soup mixture, and half of the cheeses.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake in 350°
oven for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8.

title: corn pancakes
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, pepper, milk and egg. Add corn and mix well.
Brush large skillet or griddle with butter and drop mixture by tablespoons, a few at a time.
Cook until golden brown, turn and cook on other side.
Keep warm in oven, loosely covered, until all are done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Mix 1 box Jell-O with 1 cup hot water until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into glass 9 x 13-inch dish. Refrigerate until set.

title: eggplant mozzarella
directions: Cut eggplant in 1 1/2-inch slices; divide among 4 pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Season with salt, pepper and oregano. Top each serving with onion slice and tomato half, cut side up. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and rosemary leaves.
Wrap securely in foil.
Place on grill, 3 inches from hot coals.
Cook for 30 minutes, or until eggplant is soft.
Makes 4 servings.

title: amy purvis pickles(easy, sweet)
directions: Weigh cucumbers.
For every 10 pounds of cucumbers, use the amount of ingredients as listed.
Cover washed cucumbers with strong enough brine to float an egg.
Weight down and let stand 3 weeks.
Drain.
Scald with boiling water and return to washed, scalded crock.
Cover with cold white vinegar and let stand 10 days.
Drain well; discard vinegar and cut into 3/4-inch pieces. Add and mix well together the above ingredients.
Combine with cucumber pieces, stirring well.
Stir occasionally.
That's all there is to it!
The vinegar clinging to the cucumber pieces is all the liquid you need.
The sugar will dissolve to form heavy syrup.
No sealing; no cooking.
Just keep in crock.
Very crisp.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Use 2 to 3 generously teaspoonfuls of mix to 1 cup of hot water.
Also good iced.
Yields 1 pint.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order given in a two-quart bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over top; cover well.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients and chill for 8 hours before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand for 1 hour covered with plastic wrap.
Cream together the butter and sugars; mix well.
Blend in egg-raisin mixture and oatmeal.
Mix together remaining ingredients (except nuts) and add to first mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pudding chip cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, vanilla and pudding.
Beat until smooth. Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Put together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Beat with spoon, just until blended. Slowly add melted butter, beating until smooth.
Bake in waffle iron.
Serve warm with syrup.
Or for dessert, serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: quick lasagne pie
directions: Grease baking dish, 10 x 1/2-inch pie plate.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in plate.
Mix beef, oregano, basil, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup Mozzarella; spoon over first layer.
Beat egg, milk, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into dish. Bake until knife inserted comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbles in center.

title: apricot oat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and lightly butter or spray the muffin tin.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, oats, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, stir together milk, egg, oil and vanilla until blended.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients; add milk mixture and stir just to combine.
Stir in apricots or other dried fruit.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center of one muffin comes out clean.
Take muffins from oven and place on wire rack.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing muffins from cups.
Finish cooling on rack.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken mushroom casserole
directions: In a buttered 3-quart baking dish, spread prepared rice evenly over the bottom.
Top with chicken.
Sprinkle with mushrooms.
Add black-eyed peas.
Combine mushroom soup and milk and pour over top.
Add layer of olives and top with cheese.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated through, about 45 minutes.
Can be prepared in individual servings and frozen.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Stir together ingredients.
Fill freezer with whole milk. Freeze.

title: garden chicken salad
directions: Grill and slice chicken breasts.

title: round steak supper in one dish
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper and roll in flour.
Cook onions in hot fat until tender, but not brown.
Remove onions. Brown meat slowly on both sides.
Place meat in a 3-quart casserole.
Add onions, potatoes and bay leaf.
Pour soup over. Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add green beans and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and salt in 1 cup boiling water in large bowl. Add 1/2 cup cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Put eggs in a bowl and beat in sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Put milk on to heat.
Beat flour and baking powder into eggs and sugar.
Add desired amount of flavoring.
Last, beat in hot milk.
Bake in fairly hot oven, 375° to 400°.

title: kansas city steak strips
directions: Cut meat into even strips.
Heat 1/2 the butter in a skillet. Add meat; saute over medium high heat until meat is brown and cooked to your liking.
Do not overcook.
Remove meat; keep warm. Add remaining butter to pan.
Add green onions; saute over medium high heat for 4 to 5 minutes, until onions are soft but not brown. Remove.
Add broth to pan; heat and scrape pan brownings.
Add chili sauce.
Add green beans to pan; heat for a few minutes.
Add meat and green onions; stir to blend well.
Cook over high heat for a few minutes, until mixture is hot.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in saltwater.
In saucepan, melt margarine and blend in flour.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Mix cheese sauce and macaroni together in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.

title: vulture dip
directions: Mix dry taco mix with sour cream.
Layer ingredients in large casserole dish in order given.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onions and slice about 3/8-inch thick.
Separate into rings.
Pour buttermilk into a shallow pan.
Add onion rings and allow to soak 30 minutes.
Combine egg, salt, baking powder, water, flour, 1 tablespoon salad oil, lemon juice and cayenne pepper.
Stir until smooth.

title: cabbage with caraway
directions: Melt margarine in nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray. Add shredded cabbage and next four ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Cover and cook 1 minute.

title: chicken bites
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Dip pieces into melted margarine, then into bread crumbs.
Place chicken pieces, about 1/2-inch apart on cookie sheets.
Bake uncovered until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen appetizers.

title: never fail fruit custard
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar, flour and butter.
Cream real well. Gradually fold in 2 cups milk.
Fold in egg whites that had been beaten until stiff.
Put fruit in bottom of unbaked pie shell. Pour custard on top.
Bake at 425°.
If you see it gets too brown, reduce heat to 375°
until baked.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Combine eggs, milk, mustard, nutmeg and salt in bowl; mix well. Stir in sausage, bread, cheese and parsley flakes.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Chill overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Let stand for several minutes. Cut into squares.
Yields 6 servings.

title: crunchy chews
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to a full boil,
stirring
constantly.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir
in peanut butter.
Add mixed nuts or peanuts and cereal, stirring
to coat
evenly.
Turn
into
greased
13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: banana-pineapple milkshake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until frothy.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: old henry bars
directions: In a large saucepan, heat 1/2 cup Karo syrup and sugar.
Heat until sugar is dissolved, then mix in cereal and peanut butter. After mixing, spread into a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add Pet milk and vanilla flavoring, beating all the time.
Put into ice cream freezer and finish filling freezer with plain milk.

title: chili dip
directions: In a large saucepan, combine tomatoes and Ro-Tel and bring to a boil.
Add kidney beans and bring to a boil; add chili without beans and heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Add Velveeta and simmer until cheese melts; add chili powder, mixing well, and remove from heat.
Let mixture sit, covered, overnight in refrigerator so flavors can blend.
Return to heat and add milk, stirring well.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil!
When serving, keep warm over a candle warmer or in a chafing dish.
Provide plenty of large Fritos and tostados.

title: chicken-cabbage soup
directions: Heat all ingredients, except chicken, to boiling in Dutch oven.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine the sugar, cornstarch and water.
Bring to a boil. Remove from stove and stir in jello.
When almost cool, pour strawberries in pie shell.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Place cut peppers, vinegar and sugar into blender and blend until fine.
Place mixture in large pot and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add Certo.
Stir in; place in jars immediately.
Serve on crackers spread with cream cheese.

title: louisiana hush puppies
directions: Pour enough boiling water over meal, salt, flour, chopped onion and black pepper to form a stiff mush.
Add this to milk, well beaten egg and baking powder.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep hot cooking oil.
Fry until a golden brown.
Delicious with fish.

title: sally lunn cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Pour into 2 greased pie pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 450° or until cake tests done.
Cool.
Cut into wedges and top individual servings with your favorite sliced, fresh fruit such as strawberries or peaches and top with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter-banana shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; process until smooth.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: creamy gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Drain pineapple, measuring 1/2 cup syrup. Add to gelatin. Chill until very thick. Fold in pineapple, cheese, whipped cream, cherries and almonds.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Chill until firm.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: bea's fruitcake
directions: Leave nuts, dates and fruits whole.
Sift dry ingredients together three times, sifting over fruit-nut mixture the last time. Mix well to coat all of the fruit and nuts.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Spoon into greased and wax paper lined pans. Pack slightly evenly.
Bake in slow oven, 250°, for 2 hours with a pan of water on lowest shelf.
Cover each pan with wax paper, removing last 15 minutes.
Recipe makes 1 large loaf or may use 2 smaller and shorten baking time a little.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Place in container for ice cream mixer, then add whole milk up to fill line.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Spread mixture over graham wafers; spread on cookie sheet and put in a 350° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini as directed on package; rinse with cold water. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours to blend flavors. Just before serving, add tomatoes and olives; mix lightly. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Salad can be made a day ahead and refrigerated.
Add broccoli and tomatoes just before serving to avoid discoloration.

title: sunshine fruit bars(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add juice, oil, egg product and vanilla.
Mix well; stir in fruit.
Spread into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of oats.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until lightly browned and edges pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: mexican spicy vegetable relish
directions: Peel carrots and slice diagonally into 1/2-inch chunks.
Place in a large bowl and cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 30 minutes, then drain and pour ice water over them to stop any further cooking immediately.
Slice peppers and combine with onion rings and carrots.
Blend vegetable oil, vinegar and salt.
Add to vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least one day, preferably several days.
Keeps for many months in refrigerator and improves with age.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch container with graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk.
Pour 1/2 mixture over graham crackers.
Repeat with crackers and pudding.
Top with crackers.

title: banana split
directions: First take the bananas and a bowl.
Put the two bananas in the bowl.
Next take a few cherries and some ice cream.
Then put the ice cream and cherries in the bowl on top of the bananas.
Then put a few sprinkles on top.

title: crustless egg custard(good!!!)
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar; add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into lightly greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done in preheated oven.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Cook
and
stir
bell
pepper,	pimiento
and
onion in margarine in a 10-inch skillet until onion is tender.
Stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.	Cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are brown and heated.
Serves 4.

title: cabin casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in order in Pyrex baking dish.
Cover.
Stir and skim any grease that forms periodically.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last 20 minutes.

title: parmesan cheese
directions: Mix; spoon over chicken and bake for 45 minutes at 375°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil in saucepan.
Place in crock-pot on low for 2 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt in frypan the oleo.
Add 1/3 cup of sugar; stir until dissolved.
Add pretzel sticks.
Mix together and bake on cookie sheet or cake pan for 7 minutes at 400°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with electric mixer; refrigerate.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread; cool thoroughly.
Mix together all ingredients except tomato (top with tomato if desired).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mother's pie crust(enough for 1 crust)
directions: Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger hot pot
directions: Brown hamburger into small pieces about the size of pecans, then combine all other ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
The noodles are put into the casserole just as they come from the bag. Toss to coat all ingredients.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover from casserole, with a wide spoon, turn over the top of the casserole and continue baking 30 more minutes without a cover, stir occasionally.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, butter, milk and vanilla. Pour into casserole dish.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (remember to use raw macaroni).
Let stand at least 3 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° in a covered bowl about 1 hour.

title: crumb topped baked french toast
directions: Combine first four ingredients; mix well.
Dip bread slices into egg mixture; coat both sides with crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Drizzle melted butter over crumb coated bread.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: hot apple spiced tea
directions: Combine apple juice, tea bags and cinnamon stick in a saucepan and heat slowly over medium-low heat until simmering.
Let steep for 5 minutes and then remove tea bags.
Add orange zest, cover and simmer 5 minutes and serve.
Serves 8.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *If you use bananas, be especially sure they are covered with glaze.

title: turtle cake
directions: Divide cake mix in half; to one half of the cake mix, add 1/2 cup melted butter and 1/2 can of milk.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish; cover with foil. Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: lace cookies
directions: Pour oleo over oatmeal.
Add egg and stir.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on foil and bake 11 minutes at 350°.
Cool and pull off foil.
They spread a lot so do not put them close together.

title: double delicious bars
directions: In pan, combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Press to bottom of the pan.
Next, sweetened condensed milk, chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Sprinkle coconut (if desired).
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, Karo and salt.
Boil 5 minutes.
Make 8 quarts popped corn.
Pour mixture over popped corn and mix well. Put on cookie sheet.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 200°.
Stir every 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in iron skillet until thick.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Place in pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix together and shape into a ball.
Ice with prepared cocktail sauce or mixture of ketchup and horseradish. Serve with crackers.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Make a hole in flour mixture and add cold water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Mix it all up and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grammie's brown bread
directions: Sift flours and mix everything together.
Steam for 3 hours in 2 coffee cans 2/3 full.
Delicious!

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease 12 large muffin cups. Set aside. Combine flour, sugar, poppy seeds, lemon peel, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl. Combine yogurt, lemon juice, oil, eggs and vanilla in small bowl until well blended. Stir into flour mixture just until moistened. Spoon into prepared muffin cups, filling 2/3 full. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage, drain.
Add Velveeta cheese, cut into cubes.
Season.
Spread on cocktail rye bread.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
This can be made ahead and frozen.
A man's favorite!

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain and lay flat on paper towels in single layer until needed.
Meanwhile, combine Ricotta cheese, cream cheese, milk, onion, basil, garlic powder and oregano; blend until smooth.
Add vegetables.
Spread 3/4 cup on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add a layer of noodles, 1/4 of remaining vegetable mixture and sprinkle with some of the Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: french frying batter
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch, cornmeal, salt and baking powder. Combine egg, milk and water; add to the flour mixture.
Mix quickly.
Beat with eggbeater until smooth.

title: migas rancheras
directions: Tear or cut corn tortillas into 1-inch pieces.
Cover bottom of skillet with oil.
Fry tortillas in oil over high heat.
Add tomatoes to skillet.
Stir in chopped onion and 2 to 3 jalapeno or chili peppers, diced.
Simmer until tender.

title: zucchini surprise
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sliced zucchini and onion in pan.
Fry in butter.
After about 5 minutes, add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes, then add cheese.
Cook until well blended over a medium to low heat.

title: beefy noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef with salt and pepper until done.
Add soups, water and cornstarch.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Add egg noodles, stir and cover.
Turn down heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Take cover off and let sit on low for another 10 minutes.
Great with green salad and rolls.
Enjoy!

title: tuna tart
directions: Stir eggs in a bowl with salt.
Cut scallion bulbs.
Open tuna can and open can of corn (optional).
Add half cup of cheese.
Put in the oven for half an hour.
Eat it.

title: sweet and sour brisket
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, combine first 4 ingredients.
Boil. Reduce heat and add brisket.
Spoon some mixture over meat; cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 minutes until tender.
Remove meat to platter and keep warm.
Skim off excess fat.
Combine cornstarch and water; cook until thick.
Stir and cook 2 more minutes.
Spoon some sauce over meat and pass remainder.
Garnish with parsley.

title: super brownies
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, chocolate and water.
In large bowl,
add
flour and sugar.
Pour hot chocolate mixture over it and mix well.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add soda, salt, eggs and vanilla;
mix
well.
Pour
into
broiler
pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add nuts.

title: crab puffs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Peel off leaves of biscuits, 3 leaves at a time.
On each leaf, place a small amount of mixture and bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: no eggs or war cake
directions: In saucepan, put raisins, sugar and water; boil for 3 minutes. Add shortening; set aside until cool.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add little at a time to raisin mixture and stir; mix soda with boiling water.
Add this last to cake mixture, stir well and pour into lightly greased square 9-inch cake pan; bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: texas jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool 15 to 20 minutes before cutting.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine all the vegetables in a large mixing bowl.
Bring vinegar, sugar, water, cooking oil, salt and pepper to a boil; let cool, then pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Heat cherries or blueberries, tapioca and sweetener in saucepan until it starts to thicken; set aside.
Melt diet margarine; mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into pie pan; set aside.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add cream of tartar and vanilla.
Fold in cream cheese and yogurt.
It will be a little thick.
Put into graham cracker crust and place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Put on the fruit topping and chill at least 2 hours.
You can substitute lite canned fruit for topping.
Contains 310 calories if cherry and 370 calories if blueberry.

title: summer barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to gentle boil for 15 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Enjoy over your favorite meats and vegetables.

title: frozen date salad
directions: Combine dates, nuts and pineapple.
Cream the cheese and maple syrup.
Whip the Dream Whip, then fold all together and pour in a mold (round one with the hole in the enter).
Put in freezer. Remove about half hour before serving.

title: favorite potato soup
directions: Add diced potatoes, onions, and carrots to a large 4 quart heavy or non-stick pot. Add 2 quarts of water, salt, Nature's Seasoning, dill weed, and parsley flakes. Cook until tender. Add mushroom pieces with liquid and celery soup, undiluted. If thinner soup is desired, add milk. Stir thoroughly.

title: hearty black-eyed pea soup
directions: Cook sausage, beef and onion until no longer pink; drain. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cloud jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add lemonade.
Refrigerate until jelly-like.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into a six-cup mold. Refrigerate until ready to unmold.

title: pasta vashule
directions: In a large pot, saute onion and garlic in oil; do not brown. Stir in water, tomato sauce, beans and spices.
Bring to a boil. Add pasta and boil until pasta is tender, stirring to prevent pasta from clumping or sticking to bottom of pot.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown meat.
Put rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with meat, cheese and beaten eggs with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Mix butter, cocoa and boiling water.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Bake in greased sheet pan at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: catalina taco salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Add chips and dressing just before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yankee doodle macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner as directed.
Simmer frankfurters in barbecue sauce for 5 minutes.
Combine the dinner and peas with frankfurters and serve.

title: vegetable deluxe
directions: Stir 1 minute.
Add cornstarch (1 teaspoon cornstarch and 2 teaspoons water, well blended).

title: pecan streusel coffee cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to the package directions, except stir the sour cream into the prepared batter.
Spread about two thirds of the batter into a greased and floured 13-inch x 9-inch x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle batter with the streusel mix from the package.
Carefully spread with the remaining batter.
Sprinkle with reserved nut topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool slightly in pan. Prepare glaze from the cake mix according to the package directions and drizzle over the warm coffee cake.

title: just can't leave them alone bars
directions: Mix top 3 ingredients with a fork. Keep out 1/2 of the crumbs. Pat rest of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 dish.

title: missouri cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil for about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Cool until firm.

title: super easy fish
directions: Put fish in a microwave dish.
Mix soup, apple juice and curry powder.
Pour over fish. Microwave six to eight minutes on High. Fish will flake when done.
May also be baked for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: bob's chicken or pork divine
directions: Coat meat in mixture of flour, salt, pepper and ginger. Brown meat on both sides in hot oil in frying pan on medium heat. Arrange meat in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour soup and water over meat.
Sprinkle 1/2 can onions over meat.
Bake in covered cake pan for 25 minutes at 325°.
Add remaining onions.
Bake uncovered for 15 minutes at 350°.
Take out meat and place in another pan to keep in warm oven while preparing sauce.

title: taco filling (beef)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add meat and brown.
Add other ingredients.
Yield:
12 tacos.
Carbohydrate 0 g, protein 6 g, fat 6 g, calories 78.
One serving = 1 meat low-fat exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: delores' yellow squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion into bite size pieces; steam until tender.
Drain.
Add crackers, egg, butter, salt, pepper and 3/4 pound shredded cheese. Place mixture into greased 9 1/2x11 inch pan.
Top with remainder of cheese.
Bake in 350 degrees for about 30 minutes until cheese is golden brown.
Serves a crowd.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the chocolate and oil in a saucepan over very low heat.
Cream butter until light; add the sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add melted chocolate and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and stir them into the batter with the buttermilk.
Mix the zucchini and nuts into the batter.

title: marge helm's "anyone can do it" chewy treats(or marge helm's easy treats)
directions: Mix crumbs and baking powder.
Mix milk and chips. Mix with crumbs until all is moist.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use moist fingers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cut into squares and remove from pan while still warm.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix and roll out.

title: pecan joys
directions: Chop pecans until very fine.
In large bowl, add first five ingredients and mix well.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Roll into balls.

title: cherry delight
directions: In large bowl, mix all the ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix together popcorn, peanuts, M&M's and candy corn in a large bowl. Melt together butter and marshmallows and add vanilla. Let mixture cool. Pour over popcorn mixture and stir well. Press into greased tube or Bundt pan and take out immediately. Let cake cool and cut.

title: chicken and potato saute
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Saute chicken until browned on both sides.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook about 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine flour and seasonings. Dissolve bouillon in water and stir into flour mixture.
Pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and wine or water.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: In top of double boiler, mix sugar and gelatin.
Combine lime juice and egg yolks; blend into sugar mixture.
Cook over simmering water until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lime peel and cool.
Whip cream with food coloring until stiff; fold into gelatin lime mixture.
Pour into crust. Chill until firm.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut a thin slice from the stem end of each pepper.
Wash outside and inside.
Remove all seeds and membranes. Cook peppers in boiling, salted water 5 minutes; drain.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Stuff peppers lightly with mixture.
Stand upright in a small baking dish.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes; uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Beat eggs in a small bowl, then add bananas and shortening.
Stir into dry ingredients until the mix is moist.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° until the top is firm, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 6 pieces each.
Score both ends of each piece in an X, being careful not to cut too deeply.
Brown in electric skillet.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Steam until hot dogs are cooked and "puffy".
Serve with toothpicks.

title: mamma's cobbler
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
In a glass or metal 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan that will be used to bake the cobbler, mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour boiling fruit over cake mix and bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese and confectioners sugar; cream well.
Fold in half of Cool Whip (9 ounces); spread on cool crust.
Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on package.
Cool, then spread on cream cheese mixture.
Add rest of Cool Whip (9 ounces) on top.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: tuna loaf(oven or microwave)
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place in a 7 inch souffle dish or 1-1/2 qt. microwave-save round casserole.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes without having preheated the oven, or microwave for 10 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Temperature will be 236°, soft ball stage.
Quickly stir in the last 3 ingredients in order given.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill to set.
Cut into squares.

title: cranberry glazed chicken
directions: Combine 1/2 cup flour, salt and pepper.
Skin chicken, if desired.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove chicken and drain on paper towels; keep warm. Add cranberries, brown sugar and water to pan drippings in skillet; cook for 5 minutes or until cranberry skins pop.
Blend together 1 tablespoon flour, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and vinegar.
Add vinegar mixture to cranberry mixture and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Return chicken to mixture in skillet and baste with cranberry mixture; cover and simmer 30 minutes, turning chicken occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine the sugar and flour in a large bowl. Add melted butter, eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and 2/3 of the coconut.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into shell. Sprinkle with remaining coconut. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until set.
Yields 8 servings.

title: brad's favorite cornbread
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients. Add beaten egg, milk, honey and oil. Stir just enough to mix. Bake in 2 greased 8-inch pie pans at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: butter pecan ice cream(electric freezer)
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add salt and 2 cups whole milk.
Scald over medium heat.
Add vanilla and pudding.
In a skillet, melt margarine.
Add pecans.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into freezer.
Add enough whole milk to fill line of freezer.

title: tea sparkler
directions: In large pithcer, combine all ingredients except soda.
Chill at least 2 hours. Just befor serving, add a splash of soda. Pour into ice filled glasses and garnish, if desired, with orange, lemon, or lime slices. Makes 5 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream and soup.
Salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush the crackers and mix with the melted butter. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
May be made ahead, but don't put the crumbs on until time to bake.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Chop onion and red and green peppers.
Mix vinegar, oil and sugar.
Toss all ingredients together.

title: chicken chimichanga
directions: Combine chicken, taco sauce, onion, cumin, oregano and salt in medium frypan.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: mrs. dukes' ground beef and vegetable stew
directions: In Dutch oven brown beef, breaking up with a spoon.
Add onions, garlic, water, basil, salt, pepper and potatoes.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add peppers and tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes or until all is tender.
Good with crusty bread.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Heat vinegar and sugar just enough to dissolve sugar.
Add salad oil.
Pour over vegetables and chopped onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Mix all together well.
Serve in a glass container and chill.

title: the boolymonger sandwich
directions: Spread Russian dressing on both sides of the toasted English muffin.
Put 2 ounces of turkey breast, 1 1/2 strips of bacon and 1 slice Provolone cheese on each muffin.
Slide halves under broiler until cheese melts.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain well.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add the other ingredients.
Spread on bread; place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Put in plastic bags; store in freezer. Place on a cookie sheet under broiler until done.

title: chicken 'round the world'
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Line a baking dish with foil,
and grease it.
Lie chicken on foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Put tomatoes on top of chicken.
Squirt Ranch and French dressings on top of the chicken and tomatoes.
Next, sprinkle crackers on top.
Bake in oven at 375 degrees for about 20 minutes.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Pick all bones and skin from salmon; save juice.
Mash salmon. Saute onions and bell pepper in melted butter.
Add pimento, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add eggs and milk, mixing well.
Place into a well-greased casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit and acini de pepe
directions: Drain fruit and set aside.
In saucepan, add fruit juices, sugar, beaten eggs and flour.
Cook until thick.
Pour over acini de pepe.
Mix well and chill overnight.
Add the drained cherries, oranges, pineapple and La Creme.
Mix well and serve.

title: chicken avocado melt
directions: Flatten chicken breast.
In shallow dish, mix together cornstarch, cumin and garlic salt; add chicken, one piece at a time, dredging to coat.
Mix egg and water.
In another bowl, place cornmeal.
Dip chicken first in egg and then in cornmeal, turning to coat.
In frypan, place oil and heat to medium temperature; add chicken and cook 2 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken to baking pan; place avocado slices over chicken and sprinkle cheese.
Bake in 350° oven about 15 minutes or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease and cheese melts.
Top chicken with sour cream, dividing equally; sprinkle with green onion and red pepper.
Garnish with parsley and cherry tomatoes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix in order given and sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Serves 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed. Add all ingredients except paprika and Parmesan. Mix thoroughly. Pour into greased shallow 3-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mrs. snow's mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add flour and blend well.
Add salt.
Stir in cream, stirring constantly. Add lemon juice and onion salt.
Take crust off bread and roll slices thin.
Then spread mixture on each slice of bread and roll like a jelly roll.
Freeze slightly; cut into thirds.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil together first 3 ingredients.
Add flour and sugar.
Beat together and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: kay's casserole
directions: Cook onions and celery in butter until tender, but not brown. Stir in mushrooms, pimentos, chicken and rice.
Blend broth and soup.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over salad ingredients and toss together gently.

title: ultra chicken pie
directions: Place
chicken	in greased 2 quart baking dish.
Spread vegetables	over
chicken.	Mix
soups
in a bowl.	Use can of broth to rinse soup cans and pour over vegetables and chicken. Sprinkle
black
pepper
over ingredients.	Cut margarine into self-rising
flour,
stir
milk
into
flour.
Pour
this over ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: finnish pancakes
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together all the other ingredients, pour into the pan and cook at 400°f. 200°c. gas mark 6 for 30 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: crab balls
directions: Blend cream cheese, chives, garlic powder and salt.
Fold in crabmeat.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers and vegetables.

title: hot antipasto poor boys
directions: Mix dressing and Parmesan in large bowl.
Toss with tomatoes, artichokes, pepperoni and olives.
Set oven to broil.
Place buns, knived sides facing up, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Broil with tops about 6 inches from heat until golden brown.
Spoon pepperoni mixture onto buns.
Sprinkle about 2 tablespoons Mozzarella over each.
Broil until cheese is hot and bubbly.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into greased skillet.
Bake in 450° oven until lightly browned.
Place under broiler to brown.

title: chicken wings (oriental)
directions: Blend soy sauce, sugar, oil and Five Spice powder in large bowl until sugar dissolves.
Stir in green onions.
Add chicken wings to marinade; turn to coat.
Cover chicken and refrigerate overnight. Preheat oven to 350°; drain wings, reserving marinade.
Arrange wings in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake until golden brown and tender, basting occasionally with marinade.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: party chicken tetrazzini
directions: Stew hen until tender; reserve 4 cups of the broth.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Heat butter in large saucepan and gradually blend in flour.
Slowly add the 4 cups chicken broth, then cream.
Stir over low heat until mixture has thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Combine with chicken and all other ingredients except noodles.
Boil noodles according to package directions.
Drain well and stir into chicken mixture.
Turn into two buttered 1 1/2-quart casseroles and refrigerate until ready to bake.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and heated through.
It will freeze nicely if prepared ahead of time and any leftovers will also freeze.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: uncooked fudge
directions: Melt the chocolate in a double boiler over boiling water. While it is melting, beat the egg in a big bowl; add the cream. Stir 1 cup of sugar slowly into the egg and cream.
Stir in the rest of the sugar a little at a time.
When the chocolate is melted, add mixture in the bowl.
Stir it all together until it's smooth, then pour it in a buttered cake pan.
Let the fudge harden, then cut into squares.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach; beat eggs and combine both with stuffing, etc. Form into balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 3 dozen balls.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended. Spoon into small ovenproof dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serve with crackers.

title: cranberry pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream oleo and half the sugar, then add rest of sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until fluffy.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Blend in flour, cranberries and nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan for 60 minutes.

title: spicy apple bread
directions: Mix together margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Beat with spoon for 25 strokes.
Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry mixture to egg mixture.
Add raisins and applesauce and mix.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Bread is done when you press the top and it bounces back up.
Makes 12 slice loaf.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Pack 7 jars half full of apple slices. Combine all other ingredients and bring to a rolling boil. Cover apples in jar with filling. Fill jars within 1-inch from top with apples and cover with filling. Lids should be in boiling water for 20 minutes. Place lids and rings on jars. Boil 20 minutes in a hot water bath.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add all ingredients.
Bake in cake mold about 1 hour in moderate oven at 350°.

title: summer spaghetti
directions: Toss the tomatoes, onion and olives with marinade made from the garlic, parsley, basil, capers, oregano, red wine vinegar and olive oil.
Must be refrigerated at least 6 hours to thoroughly blend flavors.
Just before serving, cook spaghetti in large kettle of boiling water.
Cook between 8 to 12 minutes; drain. Immediately toss hot pasta with cold tomato sauce.
Serve at once.

title: macaroni and chicken
directions: Chop onion; cut carrots into chunks.
In a 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat macaroni in 5 cups water to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; do not drain.

title: diabetic ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and Equal together.
