Add Coffee Rich, canned milk and instant pudding.
Mix well.
Pour in ice cream can and finish filling with milk.
You can add fruit of your choice.

title: peachy cream cheese spread
directions: Microwave cream cheese in a small glass bowl at Low for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until softened.
Add preserves and ginger; stir well.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Measure 2/3 cup cake mix into small bowl; cut in margarine. Mix in nuts and brown sugar; set aside.
Beat eggs lightly with fork.
Stir in sour cream.
Add cranberries and cinnamon.
Blend in remaining cake mix.
Pour half of batter into greased angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle on half of topping mixture (the mixture made first).
Pour in remaining batter and sprinkle on rest of topping.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients in 8-inch skillet over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted and nuts are coated, about 20 minutes.
Remove nuts from pan and cool on waxed paper.
Break apart.
Store at room temperature.
Makes 12 servings (1/4 cup each).
Contains 170 calories per serving.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine all other ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Heat until warm and pour over noodles.
Stir. Sprinkle on and stir in Parmesan cheese gradually.
You can also add cooked mushrooms or other vegetables if you wish.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Gently stir in all remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips, just until mixed.
Do not beat! Pat into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: spicy thai pizza
directions: Preheat over to 400°.
Coat 12-inch pizza pan with non-stick spray.
In large bowl combine rice, 1 cup cheese, 1/4 cup peanut butter and egg.
Press onto pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup peanut butter, water, cilantro, soy sauce, 2 tablespoons oil and red pepper.
Stir fry broccoli, onion and carrot in 1 tablespoon oil until tender crisp.
Spread peanut butter sauce over crust.
Top with vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: cashew bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and press into non-greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry sour cream mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Mix in cranberry sauce and sour cream.
Fold together and pour into mold and chill.

title: rhubarb shortcake
directions: Place rhubarb in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cream 3/4 cup sugar and oleo.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk to creamed mixture.
Spread over rhubarb.

title: turtles
directions: Melt butter and caramels in double boiler.
Add pecans.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and chill.
Melt candy quick and chocolate chips in double boiler, then dip chilled clusters and put back on cookie sheet.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Pound steak with flour and salt.
Brown meat.
Blend remaining flour and vegetables in pan drippings. Bake covered in 350° oven until tender for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blanch the peppers and set aside.
In large skillet, saute the onion in oil until softened.
Add sausage; saute until browned.
Remove skillet from the heat; add bread crumbs, cheese and egg whites and mix well.
Cut peppers lengthwise, then stuff with sausage mixture.
Place into baking dish; bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Place bread into a greased 3-quart casserole. Beat eggs in a bowl; beat in sugar, milk and vanilla. Pour mixture over bread and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until puffed, brown and firm to the touch in the center. Serve hot or cold with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: almond crescents
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape dough into balls or crescents. Bake approximately 7 to 8 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: shortcut lasagne
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, water and spaghetti sauce.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, begin layering meat sauce, uncooked noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and the rest of the sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: florine's chocolate cake
directions: Beat well; add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add to butter mixture.
Mix flour and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Mix vinegar and soda (this will foam).
Add to batter and gently stir until well mixed.
Pour into 2 or 3 cake pans and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: linguine ai gamberi(easy sauce while pasta cooks)
directions: Saute the chopped onion in a pan until clear; add butter and 1/2 olive oil first.
When simmers, add the dry vermouth.
Add shrimp (cleaned and deveined).
In a deep serving bowl, add the tomatoes, parsley and garlic.
Remove the shrimp from the saute. Add the cooked (al dente) pasta to the serving bowl; toss, then arrange the shrimp and garnish.
Never use grated cheese with any seafood dish, it is not only uncouth, but will insult the chef. Serve hot immediately.
Guests will rave!
"No cheese with seafood".

title: apple crisp
directions: Set oven at 350°. Grease a 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.

title: julie's chocolate pecan candy
directions: Melt together the chips in microwave-add pecans-pour out on wax paper in clusters.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn. Melt butter in a saucepan and add sugar, Karo and salt. Let come to a boil. Cook 5 more minutes without stirring. Take off heat and add vanilla and soda. Put popcorn in a long pan. Add nuts and pour sauce over popcorn and nuts. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes. Take out of oven and place on wax paper. Separate with hands. Store in a covered container.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut ham up in small pieces.
Mix all together.
Form into a ball and roll in nuts.
Makes 2 small cheese balls.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oats.
Mix well.
Bring to boil.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add oats.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto buttered foil.
Cool before eating.

title: fast tartar sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well. Serve or cover and chill until ready to use.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple (not drained), bananas and 1/2 c. chopped pecans, if desired.
Put 3 cups of mixture in oblong pyrex dish.
Refrigerate and let set.
Spread sour cream over mixture.
Add remaining mixture and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hearty multi-grain bread(makes 3 loaves)
directions: Warm juice, quick oats, cracked wheat (optional) and butter or margarine just until butter begins to melt.
Let cool.
Combine yeast, sugar and water in a small bowl and let proof.
In a large bowl, blend rye flour, wheat germ, salt, 2 1/2 cups of the bread flour and the whole wheat flour.
Make a well in the center and pour in warmed liquid.
Add honey, molasses, eggs and yeast mixture.
Mix with large wooden spoon until generally blended.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add water, sugar, oregano, bay leaf and garlic.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 3 hours.
Yields 10 servings.

title: jazzberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs, oil and milk, add to dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 full with batter.
Dot generously with preserves; top with remaining batter, filling pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: aunt justine's lettuce soup
directions: Saute chopped onions in bottom of a soup pot until golden brown.
Depending on how much soup you want to make, add 2 to 4 quarts of water to the pot.
Add cut up potatoes, again depending on the amount of soup you want and the size of the potatoes (add 2 to 6 more).
After potatoes are thoroughly cooked, mash them while in soup pot.
Add 2 bouillon cubes.
Add torn dark green lettuce leaves to soup.
Cook additional 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: golden parmesean potatoes
directions: Put dry ingredients in a plastic bag.
Peel potatoes, rinse and cut into large cubes.
Melt the butter in a 9x13 pan.
While potatoes are wet put a few at a time in bag and shake.
Then put in pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour turning potatoes after 1/2 hour.
Some times it takes longer to make them crispy.

title: water chestnut dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except vegetables and keep in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Put lukewarm
water,
yeast,
salt, sugar and butter in mixing bowl.
Let	stand 10 minutes.
Combine flour, dry milk, egg and grated cheese.
Add mix to liquid ingredients.
Knead with	hoop until dough leaves side of	bowl.
Let
rise
until double bulk. Shape;
put in baking pan.	Let
rise.
Bake
at 400° until brown.

title: ma duran's pound cake
directions: Measure flour; set aside.
Separate eggs and beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Beat oleo, sour cream, sugar, soda, egg yolks and flavorings together.
Add flour gradually. Fold in egg whites.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: silver turtles
directions: You will need 4 (10 x 10-inch) foil squares.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Take a sheet of foil and place 1/4 pound of ground beef. Place a few potatoes and carrots, onions and 1/4 package broccoli on it.
Add seasonings.
Fold foil into a pouch.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: freezer fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in cream over low heat.
Mix raisins, pineapple, cracker crumbs, cherries, coconut and English walnuts. Mix well in large bowl.
Pour milk and melted marshmallows over the six ingredients and mix well.
Mold into a Bundt pan.
Press firmly and freeze for 30 days.
Let thaw in Kelvinator for 2 days before serving.

title: ginger tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar and mix well.
Add syrup and salt.
Mix 1 heaping teaspoon soda to 1/2 cup hot coffee.
Add remaining soda to remaining coffee; add to liquids, add ginger, then flour.
May be rolled and cut, dropped and lightly patted down; or pinched off and patted out.
Bake at 350° until done.
Do not overcook.
Approximately 3 dozen large cookies.

title: polly's brownies
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour over rhubarb in a 9-inch pastry-lined pan.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soak minced dried onion in Worcestershire sauce for 15 minutes.
Then combine with cheeses and lemon juice.
Roll into ball shape; then roll into crushed pecans until covered.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Boil broccoli, onion and celery for about 6 to 10 minutes or until slightly tender. Do not overcook. Drain broccoli mixture and combine with 1 cup Minute rice. Heat all other ingredients slowly in saucepan until smooth and creamy.
Spread broccoli mixture into buttered casserole dish. Pour sauce mixture over broccoli. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: crisp skillet chicken with gravy
directions: Dust chicken with flour.
Brown chicken in butter.
Add water. Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until done. Uncover last 10 minutes to crisp chicken.
Remove chicken; add gravy.
Heat, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Serve with chicken.
Serves 4.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix together the butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add the flour, salt and chopped pecans.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: Put water in saucepan.
Add gelatin and heat until gelatin dissolves.
Set aside.
In blender, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add gelatin mixture.
Blend and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: leprechaun mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in medium saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup of sugar, salt and egg yolks; stir until thoroughly blended. Place over low heat; stir constantly until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly, about 5 minutes.

title: five star chili
directions: Cook hamburger, onions and garlic until done. Stir in tomato juice, tomato sauce, chili powder, oregano and cumin. Stir together. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add chili beans with sauce. Continue simmering for 1 hour longer, stirring occasionally. Serve and enjoy.

title: fried blossoms
directions: Gather a pan of pumpkin or squash blossoms when fully opened. Remove stamens and wash and drain the petals.
Make a batter using 1 egg, flour and milk.
Dip the blossoms in batter, then drop into deep hot fat.
Serve as a vegetable.
MMM good.

title: curried lentils
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until done, about 60 minutes.
Serve over generous portions of steamed rice.
Serves 4.
Contains 1% fat.

title: cucumber salad oriental
directions: Combine all ingredients except sesame seed and mix well.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in oil until tender. Place biscuit mix in a bowl. Combine eggs and milk just until combined. Stir in onion, 1 cup of cheese and 4 teaspoons of parsley. Spread the batter into 2 greased round baking pans. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and parsley. Drizzle with butter. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and top of bread is lightly brown. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: toffee bars
directions: Sift flour and salt. Cream margarine, adding sugar and beating well until light & fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well. Stir in flour to make a smooth dough. Spread evenly in 13x9 pan and bake in a 350 degree oven for about 18 minutes or until done. Melt chocolate chips.
Spread over surface of cookies while warm and sprinkle at once with nuts.
Cut into bars.

title: easy rhubarb jam
directions: Put on low heat all ingredients except Jell-O.
Stir until clear and thick.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir.
Makes 3 1/3 pints.

title: down south sausage pie
directions: Prepare crust, turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead for one minute.
Fit into 9-inch pie plate.
Prebake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; add sugar and beat together. In another bowl, combine pineapple, frozen strawberries, nuts, bananas and whipped topping; mix thoroughly but gently. Combine with cream cheese mixture. Spoon into loaf pan (8 1/2 x 3-inch). Freeze overnight. Serve frozen. Serves 12. Keep 4 to 6 weeks wrapped in freezer.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off grease.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Cook noodles 16 minutes.
Beat eggs into cottage cheese.

title: stove top stuffing
directions: Heat butter in a large pan.
Saute the first 2 ingredients in the butter for about 10 minutes.
Stir in croutons; add the chicken broth, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper, stirring constantly on low flame.

title: corn chowder
directions: Simmer the water, onion, celery, potatoes and parsley until half cooked, about 10 minutes.
Add the corn.
Simmer gently with the other vegetables until nearly done, not more than a few minutes.
Add milk and bring the soup just to boiling point without actually boiling.
Add seasonings to taste.

title: cabbage with mustard sauce(our favorite way to serve cabbage)
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring 2 inches of water to a boil.
Add cabbage; cover and cook until tender-crisp, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
While cabbage is cooking, melt margarine in a small saucepan.
Stir in onion flakes.
Blend flour with 2 tablespoons water.
Add to margarine, stirring.
Add salt, pepper, milk and 1/2 cup water.
Cook, stirring, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in horseradish and mustard.
Place cabbage in 4 small serving bowls.
Spoon sauce evenly over cabbage.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, and place in a large ovenproof bowl.
Put cheese on top and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter for topping in a 9-inch pan or a square pan. Sprinkle brown sugar on butter, then place pineapple in pan.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder, salt and water together.
Place batter on topping.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: overnight caramel strata
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and stir over medium-low heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring to boil.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and coat pan bottom evenly with the mixture.
Then arrange 6 slices of bread in a single layer on top of the caramel layer, trimming bread to fit.
Cover with remaining bread.
Whisk the rest of the ingredients and pour over the bread.
Cover and chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 40 minutes or until bread is puffed and light golden brown.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Invert portions or the entire pan on serving plate.
Garnish with fruit.

title: balsamic vinaigrette
directions: Lightly whisk together vinegar, egg white, mustard, herbs, salt and pepper. Slowly add oil, while continuing to beat the dressing.

title: parmesan snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on small rye bread slices.
Place a slice of green olive on top.
Broil until golden brown.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix together melted margarine, coconut, nuts and milk.
Add sugar.
Grease hands with margarine and form mixture into small balls.
Place on waxed paper and chill for about 15 minutes.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in a deep pan.
Dip candy balls in chocolate mixture.

title: strawberry angel pink dessert
directions: Arrange cake pieces in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat pudding, milk and ice cream.
Pour over pieces of cake.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add frozen berries.
Pour over pudding and cake. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: skillet corned beef hash
directions: Fry potatoes and onion in hot oil until brown.
Drain oil. Add sage and black pepper; stir.
Add broken corned beef until the beef is heated through.
This is good served with Skillet Cabbage as a side dish.

title: zucchini spice cake
directions: Mix in large bowl first 4 ingredients.
Beat well until creamy.
Combine next 6 ingredients and add to mixture, last of all add zucchini.
Nuts and raisins are optional.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Add enough water to crushed pineapple to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add sugar and bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O and vinegar and let cool. Whip the Milnot which has been refrigerated overnight (or cream). When first part has thickened, add 1 cup American cheese, nuts and cherries.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream
shortening

Add salt and eggs, one

Add yeast which has been dissolved in warm water.

Place in well-greased

When ready to use, take out amount needed and punch down.
Knead on floured pastry

Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter. Brush top with melted butter. Fold over in pocketbook fashion. Cover with clean

and let rise at room temperature for one hour.
Bake at 450° until brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 5 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crunch 'n franks
directions: Coat each frank with barbecue sauce and then roll it in the chips. Let stand for 30 minutes to set.
Grill about four inches from the coals, about 2 minutes on each side or until coating is browned and the franks are hot.
Serve in buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients, but ribs, together.
Place ribs in the bottom of a baking dish.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nanny's king ranch chicken
directions: Layer chips on bottom of large casserole dish.
Pour chicken broth over chips.
Layer all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour onions
directions: Slice onions and arrange in 1-quart baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the onions.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: nut cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Add in shortening.
Measure 2/3 cup milk and flavoring; add and beat for two minutes.
Add remaining milk and eggs; beat for 2 minutes more.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
In
a separate bowl, make a paste out of food coloring and cocoa, then add to cream mixture. Add salt, flour, vanilla and buttermilk, then remove from
mixer. Mix
in
(don't
beat)
vinegar and baking soda. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: company pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all together and put in pie crust.
Can be frozen or refrigerated.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together; roll out for size pie you are making.
Makes two 9-inch pie crusts.

title: crab soup
directions: Heat all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Chop green onion or chives on top.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
In another bowl beat together until smooth the Ricotta cheese, vanilla, sugar and eggs. Pour over the cake.
Place in a 350° oven and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Combine Cool Whip and almond extract; blend.
Spread over cooled cake.

title: chili-tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Combine ground beef and onion in large skillet.
Cook and stir until meat is browned.
Drain off excess grease.
Stir in tomato sauce, Worcestershire, salt, pepper, garlic and chili powder.
Heat through.
Add spaghetti and add pinto beans.
Combine cheese and olives in small bowl.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish half the beef mixture, half the cheese mixture, tortillas, remaining beef mixture and remaining cheese mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: micro curried chicken
directions: Place onion and garlic in 1 3/4-quart casserole dish.
Cook covered 2 minutes on High until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, curry powder, bouillon and red pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook uncovered on High for 5 minutes until mixture thickens and bubbles, stirring twice.
Stir in chicken.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Serve over rice with chopped peanuts and sliced green onions.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package instructions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut over cake while hot. Then let cake cool completely. Top with Cool Whip and then coconut. Refrigerate before serving.

title: silver spoon spread
directions: Cream together all ingredients except bread.
Place creamed mixture in refrigerator overnight.
Form into a ball and serve on warmed French baguette.

title: jumbos
directions: Mix eggs, mushroom soup, milk, pepper and poultry seasoning together.
Tear bread into tiny crumbs and add to first mixture. Add lean ground beef; blend well.
Melt shortening in skillet. Spread mixture in pan.
Separate sliced onion rings and spread over mixture.
Cover and cook 20 minutes over medium heat.
Stir Cheddar cheese soup, undiluted, and spoon over meat and onions; cover and heat through, about 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Delicious served with fried rice.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick and water to make dough. Spread thin in about a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown hamburger, onion, bouillon, garlic and peppers.
Drain.
Mix tomato sauce, oregano and mushrooms with tomato mixture.
Spoon over dough. Top with cheese.
Bake about 20 minutes or until brown in a 425° oven.

title: german potato salad
directions: Wash and boil potatoes.
Cool, then peel. Dice potatoes and onion into large casserole dish. Cut up bacon into small pieces and fry. Drain excessive drippings. Thicken remaining with 2 rounded tablespoonfuls of flour.
Add to potatoes.
Bring to a boil on stovetop the sugar, vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
Pour liquid ingredients over the potatoes.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: southwest soup
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook, stirring occasionally, until soup is thoroughly heated. Good served with corn bread.

title: catfish gumbo
directions: Cut fish into 1-inch pieces.
Cook celery, pepper, onions and garlic in vegetable oil in Dutch oven until tender.
Add broth, tomatoes, okra, red pepper, file, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Place fish on vegetables.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Serve with hot rice.

title: banana dog
directions: Open hot dog bun.
Spread peanut butter inside.
Pour or spoon a little honey over the peanut butter in a zigzag pattern.
Peel banana.
Place it in bun and eat.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender; drain water from Veg-All and place in a large mixing bowl.
Add soup and milk; stir.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Divide ingredients into 2 pie crusts.
Place other pie shells on top.
Cut slits in top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon gooey
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Put into a greased 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread this on top of first mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
For variety, chocolate cake mix can be used.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute squash and onion in butter until tender.
Onion will be clear.
Use a potato masher or fork to mash up squash and onion mixture.
Crumble cornbread or hush puppies in the food processor.
Add egg, cornbread, soup and spices to the squash mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Bake, uncovered 20 - 25 min.
Serves 4 - 6.

title: mushroom fettuccine
directions: In medium skillet, heat oil.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add mushrooms, garlic and basil; saute 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Stir in sour cream.
Add fettuccine; toss to coat.
Heat thoroughly (do not boil).
Sprinkle with pepper.
Makes 2 servings.
Can double.

title: punch for a brunch
directions: Mix well.
When ready to serve, add 1 quart of ginger ale. Pour over crushed ice.
Serve orange and lemon in punch bowl.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out and use as any pie crust recipe.

title: grandma's soft rolled molasses cookies
directions: Combine egg, sugar, molasses and margarine.
Add water with soda added.
Add ginger, cloves, salt and cinnamon.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll out on floured board and cut. Bake in 400° oven just until they do not dent when touched lightly. Do not overbake.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Keeps well in a tightly closed can.

title: becky's "killer" cake
directions: Mix oranges with cake mix.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean pilaf
directions: Chop onion.
Melt butter in pan.
Add onion; cook.
Chop mushrooms.
Add to onions and saute.
Add tarragon and rice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly for 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Wash and trim green beans in 1-inch pieces.
Cook in water with a little salt for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Gently fold green beans into rice. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: b. j.'s cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
(Do not use mixer.)
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes in a buttered and lightly floured pan (9 x 13 x 2-inches).
Cool and cut into squares.
(This is easy, quick and good!) Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion until the beef is browned. Drain. Stir in picante sauce, beans, salt and pepper. Set aside. In a small bowl, combine cottage cheese and egg. Spread 1/3 of meat mixture in bottom of one 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Top with half of Monterey Jack, half of cottage cheese mixture and 6 tortillas. Tear tortillas if necessary to cover cheese. Repeat layers, ending with meat. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes; garnish with green onions. Serve with sour cream.

title: dandelion greens
directions: Pick over carefully (they can be used until they bloom).
Wash in several waters.
Put in boiling water with a piece of salt pork.
Boil 1 hour.
Drain well.
Add salt (to taste) to boiling water; boil 2 more hours.
When well done and tender, turn into colander and drain.
Goes well with soup beans and onions.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in 1-quart jar.
Cover tightly.
Shake jar vigorously to blend ingredients.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil the hen in the water and salt until tender, about 3 to 4 hours.
(Save broth for mixing dressing.)
Mix crumbled bread in a large bowl with broth to resemble unbaked corn bread; don't leave it too dry.
Add water or *canned broth, if needed. Pour into large baking pan and bake at 450° for 1 hour or until done.

title: beef tips
directions: Brown steak in oleo.
Add garlic salt or powder, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, onion soup mix and chopped green pepper. (Or use large pieces of pepper and take out before serving if you wish.)
Add water and simmer until meat is tender.
(May need to add a bit more water while meat is simmering; simmer about 45 to 60 minutes.)
Thicken gravy and serve over rice or noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until it looks like crumbs.
Put half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread thinly sliced apples over flour mixture and sprinkle granulated sugar over apples.
Beat eggs, sour cream and vanilla together.
Pour over apples.
Top with remaining flour mixture and walnuts.
Bake in oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken how-so
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
In skillet, brown chicken in margarine or butter until golden brown.
Stir in soup, water, bouillon cube, soy sauce, Worcestershire, curry and poppy seed; mix well.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the bamboo shoots, celery, onion and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in green pepper and wine. Cover and simmer 2 to 3 minutes more.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: beef and noodles(serves 6 to 8)
directions: After slicing steak, season with pepper.
Heat 12-inch skillet.
Add steak; cook until all liquid out of steak and it is browned.
Add mushroom soup and 1/2 can or less of water.
Stir thoroughly until bubbly.
Reduce heat to simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook egg noodles as directed.
Serve beef and sauce over noodles.

title: apple pie
directions: Place apples in pie crust.
Top with 1/2 c. sugar and cinnamon.
In a small bowl, mix flour, 1/2 c. sugar, and margarine.
Work together and spoon on top of pie.
Press down with fingers.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 300 degrees.

title: agression cookies
directions: Put all together and knead. Form small balls on ungreased cookie sheet. Butter bottom of small glass, dip into sugar, press cookies flat.

title: sam's coconut surprise
directions: Melt oleo; remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and coconut. Blend well.
Shape into balls.
Make well in center of each and place on cookie sheet.
Now fill the well with the melted chocolate.
Chill until firm.

title: cookie mix
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Add dry milk and mix well.
Mix in shortening until the mixture looks like coarse corn meal.
Store in tightly covered jar or can.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, and butter together.
In another bowl, mix milk and pudding together, then add Cool Whip to pudding.
Blend the pudding mixture into the bowl with the cream cheese mixture.
Crumble cookies.
Layer the mixture in a large bowl or flower pot starting and ending with cookies. Refrigerate until serving.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Mix yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and warm water; set aside. Scald milk; add shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour to make a batter.
Add yeast mixture and beaten eggs; beat well.
Add 5 more cups flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Knead and place in greased bowl.
Cover and rise about 2 hours.
Roll about 1/4-inch and spread with melted butter, sugar and cinnamon; add nuts or raisins if desired.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Will also need gallon jar.
Do not refrigerate.
Keep lid loose.

title: hot grapefruit salad
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil until brown.
Add sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and grapefruit juice.
Simmer until mixed and sugar is dissolved.
Arrange grapefruit sections on a lettuce leaf, making 4 individual salad plates.
Pour mixture over each equally. Serve hot or place in refrigerator to cool.

title: confetti salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add vinegar, salt and ice cubes; stir constantly until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Spoon or pour into individual molds or a 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve on greens with mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: saucy stuffed peppers
directions: Cut 1/4-inch slice from top of each pepper; remove seeds. Cook green peppers in boiling water 5 minutes. Brown sausage in a skillet until slightly browned; drain off excess fat. Combine meat, oats and tomato juice. Fill peppers with meat mixture. Place in baking dish; add small amount of water. Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except parsley.
Form into a ball and roll in fresh chopped parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: grandma stolley's frikadellen(meatballs)
directions: Soak roll in water; squeeze out excess water and mix well with remaining ingredients.
Shape mixture into round patties about 2 to 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Brown on both sides in hot shortening.
Set aside.
Drain grease from skillet and make brown gravy (can use envelope of brown gravy mix if desired).
Return meatballs to the gravy and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pinch off small amount; roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: quickest of quick hot chicken pot pie
directions: Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Ingredients bought and stored ahead can be combined in minutes for unexpected guests at meal time.

title: hamburger hot pot
directions: Saute hamburger until browned.
Combine with rest of ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Do not pre-cook the noodles.
Toss to mix thoroughly.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn over the top ingredients so that they will get the benefit of the juice.
Bake 30 minutes longer, uncovered.
Stir occasionally to insure even cooking of the noodles.

title: homemade turkey dressing
directions: Cook potatoes and drain.
Combine all ingredients until mixture is kind of dry.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: cavitini
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper in skillet; drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes with lid.
Add cooked macaroni to other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish. Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° or until cheese melts. Serve with salad and French bread.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Place wafer in bottom of liner (use 12 cupcake liners) in a cupcake pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg, vanilla and lemon juice until light and fluffy.
Fill liners 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with spoonful of pie filling and chill. Makes 12.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine 1 envelope taco seasoning mix, refried beans and red pepper in a bowl and mix well.

Combine the remaining envelope of taco seasoning mix and the sour cream in a bowl and mix well. Layer the bean mixture, avocado dip, sour cream mixture, lettuce, cheese, tomatoes, olives and green onions in a large serving bowl. Yields 40 servings.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in shortening until brown.
Add other ingredients and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: sinigang sa miso
directions: Clean and cut fish into 5 to 6 pieces.
Wash mustard greens and cut in half.
Saute garlic, onion and tomatoes in hot oil until mushy; add miso sauce and patis.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Add milkfish and 2 cups water; bring to a boil (boil about 10 minutes).
Add mustard greens and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in lemon juice.
Add patis, if desired.
Remove from heat.
Serve hot.

title: ruby's mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by spoonful on greased pan; bake at 350°.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Cut meat into desired sizes.
Salt and pepper meat.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Dip meat into egg and milk mixture; roll in cracker crumbs (press crackers on).
Fry in Crisco oil.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan.
Stir all ingredients in pan with fork until moistened; beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.

title: chocolate coconut pudding
directions: Prepare pudding, using mixing instructions on box.
Add coconut and mix well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mixture for a hangover
directions: Blend in glass and fill with soda.
Use half mixture and half soda.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Spread cream cheese over medium to large platter.
Layer with sour cream and salsa.
Add or sprinkle cheese, lettuce (optional), olives and tomato.
Put in fridge for 1 hour before serving. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry cream dessert
directions: In a bowl combine cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Reserve 1/4 cup of crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining crumbs on bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
In a saucepan mix the remaining 1/2 cup sugar and gelatin. Add 3/4 cup cold water.
Heat and stir until gelatin and sugar dissolve.
In a bowl combine sour cream and yogurt.
Gradually blend gelatin mixture.
Add vanilla.
Chill until partially set. Whip cream to soft peaks, fold in blueberries and pour over crust. Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top and chill until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: valna ford's koko cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll in waxed paper and chill.
Slice and bake.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix well and chill several hours before serving with crackers.

title: pineapple dream
directions: Mix graham crackers, oleo and sugar. Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan for crust. Mix cream cheese with sugar with electric mixer. Make pudding. Mix pudding with cheese and spread over crust. Put drained pineapple on next layer. Top with Cool Whip.

title: spicy thai chicken pasta
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, cook noodles until tender, 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain well.
Return pan to low heat and add peanut butter and water, mixing until well blended.
Remove from heat and add rice vinegar, sesame oil, soy sauce, hoisin sauce, hot chili oil, sugar, garlic powder and ginger; mixing until blended.
Stir in carrots, scallions, cucumber, red pepper and chicken until mixed well.
Add noodles and toss.
Serve on a bed of shredded lettuce and garnish with tomatoes and crisp noodles or bean sprouts.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, egg, onion, salt, pepper, 1/4 cup crumbs and half of the butter.
Top with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken a la creole
directions: Rinse the chicken well.
Simmer the chicken to make a stock. After the chicken is boiled, remove from stock, let cool and then debone and save meat.
In a large, high-walled skillet, heat the olive oil over medium-high heat and saute the onion, bell pepper, parsley and green onions until the onions are clear.
Then add the mint, garlic, wine and stock.
Stir in the tomatoes and soy sauce; bring to a boil.
Add the chicken, salt and pepper and bring back to a boil.
Turn the heat down to low and simmer, covered, for at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked rice. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked whole red snapper
directions: Have head and fins removed from fish.
Crumble bay leaves and place inside of cavity.
Place fish in lightly greased lined baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over fish.
Bake uncovered in preheated oven at 350° about 25 minutes, basting often with sauce until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack firmly into ungreased pan, 8 x 10.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
May have to drain off excess grease.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: While sweet potato is still warm, add shortening and honey. Cream well, then beat in egg.
In lukewarm water, dissolve yeast. Stir milk into potato mixture, then add yeast.
Add enough sifted flour to make stiff dough.
On floured board, knead dough well, then move to large greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk. Return to floured board and knead slightly.
Place back in bowl; cover tightly.

Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours before baking time. Pinch off desired amount of dough and shape into cloverleaf rolls. (Cloverleaf = in each cup of well oiled muffin tin, place 3 (1-inch) balls of dough.)
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 15 minutes until browned.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer macaroni and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over macaroni.
Dot top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: berry banana smoothie(yields 2 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Cover and process for approximately 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour immediately into two tall glasses and serve.

title: succotash
directions: Cook lima beans according to package directions.
When almost done, add corn and other ingredients.
Cook until lima beans are done, then serve.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Make jello according to directions and allow to congeal slightly.
Layer 1/2 of the cake (broken into small pieces) in bottom of dish.
Add a layer of 1/2 the strawberries, 1/2 the jello and 1/2 the Cool Whip.
Repeat the first 3 layers (cake, berries, jello).
Add final layer of Cool Whip when ready to serve.
Safe for diabetics.
Exchanges:
2/3 cup = 1/3 fat, 1/2 bread and 1/6 fruit.

title: rice stuffing with pine nuts and rosemary
directions: In a kettle, bring 6 quarts water to a boil with the salt; sprinkle in the rice, stirring until the water returns to a boil, and boil for 10 minutes.
Drain the rice in a large colander over a kettle of boiling water and steam the rice, covered with a kitchen towel and the lid, for 15 minutes, or until it is fluffy and dry.
Let the rice cool; transfer it to a large bowl and cover it with plastic wrap.
In a skillet, cook the onion in the butter over moderately low heat, stirring, until it is softened; remove the skillet from the heat and stir in the rosemary and 1/2 cup broth.

Add to the rice the onion mixture, the scallion greens, the parsley, the pine nuts and salt and pepper to taste; stir the stuffing until it is combined well and let it cool completely before stuffing.

The stuffing can also be baked separately by spooning it into a shallow baking dish, moistening it with additional 3/4 cup broth and bake it, covered, in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Makes about 8 cups uncooked stuffing or enough for a 14-pound turkey.
Adjust amount of ingredients for smaller turkey or chicken.

title: salted nut roll
directions: Melt peanut butter chips and oleo together until smooth.
Add milk and marshmallows.
Pour over salted peanuts that are put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Can save some to pour on top.)
I put in microwave to melt marshmallows slightly so they stick together better.)

title: yummy granola
directions: Soften dates
in
cup
hot water.
Blend dates and water. Add
bananas
and vanilla and blend.
Mix dry ingredients in
a large bowl.
Add blended mixture to dry ingredients thoroughly. Crumble and bake on sprayed cookie sheets at 150° overnight or at 300°
for
90 minutes, stirring every 30 minutes.
Add 1 cup dried fruit prior to serving.
Makes approximately 9 cups.

title: mustard grilled chicken
directions: Stir together 1/3 cup mustard, 1 tablespoon cayenne pepper, vegetable oil and vinegar.
Place chicken in a large food storage bag.
Pour in mustard mixture.
Press out air and seal tightly. Massage gently to distribute the marinade.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or longer.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Grill chicken, turning frequently.
Baste with mustard mixture.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion together. Drain. Add spices to meat and both jars of salsa. Spray casserole dish with Pam. Place layer of tortillas (usually 2), then layer meat and cheeses. Continue layering and end with cheese on top. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. When serving, use sour cream, lettuce, onions, olives or salad to the side.

title: country style meat casserole
directions: *Add water to remainder of tomato sauce to fill can; set aside.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Trim fat from meat; rub with garlic.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Pound flour mixture into both sides of meat.
Add onion and brown.
Add water and undiluted chicken/rice soup.
Cook uncovered over low heat for an hour or so.
Before serving, add mushrooms, mushroom soup (undiluted), parsley and about 1 cup sour cream.
Careful not to boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: avgolemono sauce(for stuffed grapevine leaves)
directions: The secret in preparing the sauce so it will not curdle is to pour hot broth from the main dish into the eggs while they are being beaten.
This procedure heats the eggs to the same temperature and eliminates curdling.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into mixing bowl; blend well.
Bring to rapid boil in saucepan the oleo, shortening, water and cocoa; pour over flour-sugar mixture and mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients and add all at once to batter, mixing well.
Pour into greased, lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until it tests done.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a saucepan, mix the first five ingredients
and heat until margarine is melted.
Remove from heat.
Separate eggs; set white aside in grease free bowl. Maintain at room temperature.
Slowly add 8 tablespoons of heated liquid to egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Pour yolks into remainder of heated mixture.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water and add milk/egg mixture.
Over medium heat, bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate until cool.
Bake pie shell in oven for 15 minutes or until brown; add peanut butter to cooled pudding.
Mix well and pour into cooled pie shell.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, honey and salt.
Stir in the milk gradually. Add vanilla.
Pour into custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set cups in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° (slow oven) 30 to 40 minutes or until the tip of a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: (microwave) lazy day lasagna
directions: Crumble ground meat in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, until no longer pink, stirring once, and drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, basil, oregano, garlic powder and water.
Cover with lid. Microwave 4 to 5 minutes, until mixture boils.
Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg and parsley; mix well.

title: pecan roll
directions: Work sugar and vanilla into marshmallow cream.
Shape in a roll.
Wrap in wax paper and freeze overnight.
Melt the caramels in a double boiler.
Dip frozen rolls in melted caramels, then roll in chopped nuts.
Lay on wax paper and let set.
Rewrap. Tastes better after they set a few days.
Slice them and serve. Rolls may be made in your choice of sizes.

title: glogg nog
directions: Beat eggs on low speed of electric mixer until blended.
Add sugar and spices.
Beat at medium speed until sugar is dissolved. On low speed, beat in softened ice cream.
Add the juices.
Cover and chill.
To serve, pour ice cream mixture into a large punch bowl.
Slowly pour in ginger ale, stirring with an up and down motion.
Add ice ring to punch bowl, if desired.
For each serving, sprinkle nutmeg atop and add a stick cinnamon stirrer, if desired.
Makes 17 cups.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Mix and pour into a pie crust.
Crumble up graham crackers on top.

title: creamy cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll dough to 18 x 6-inch rectangle.
Brush with melted butter. Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough.
Roll up jelly roll fashion from long side; moisten edges and seal.
Cut into 20 slices.
Place rolls, cut side down, in two 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
Let rise until double (about 1 1/2 hours). Pour cream over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
While warm, drizzle top with confectioners sugar glaze (sugar mixed with milk).

title: seafood risotto
directions: In large skillet, toast rice in 1/4 cup olive oil until browned.
Add wine, then heated clam juice.
Gradually add boiling water until rice absorbs all liquid.
Saute onion and garlic in 1/4 cup olive oil.
Then add shrimp and scallops and brandy.
Cook until clear.
Serve over the rice.

title: stuffed cabbage, polish style
directions: Remove core of cabbage. Place whole head in large pot of boiling salted water. Cover and cook approximately 5 minutes or until soft enough to remove outer leaves. Remove the thick center stem from each outer leaf. Saut onion in oil. Cook rice. Mix meat, onions, rice, seasonings and egg together in a large bowl. Place 2 teaspoons of meat mix on each cabbage leaf and roll. Place rolls in large pot. Chop leftover cabbage and place on top of rolls. Pour diluted tomato soup on top. Cover and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: horseradish cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese.
Add remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve with crackers.
Double recipe for large crowd.

title: mushroom casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute mushrooms.
Add flour and parsley.
Cook 10 minutes over a slow flame.
Add light cream, juice of 1/2 lemon and paprika. Mix and add egg mixture.
Place in flat casserole and top with cracker crumbs, mixed with 1/4 pound melted butter.
Heat at 375° until top gets brown and bubbly.

title: raspberry sherbet dessert
directions: Stir together and refreeze before serving.
Can be served in hollowed out orange halves with sprig of mint for garnish.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Mix cream cheese, mushroom soup and onion in saucepan.
Simmer over low heat until melted.
Mix gelatin in 1/2 cup hot water. Stir into cream cheese mixture.
Add mayonnaise, celery and tuna. Stir well.
Pour into 6 cup mold. Chill overnight.
Serve on chilled plate with crackers.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Stir together soup, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Mix with all other ingredients except cheese and onion rings.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove.
Cover with onion rings.
Put foil over.
Cook at 350° for 3 minutes longer.

title: dressed bananas
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients. Stir and thicken on stove or in microwave (High about 2 1/2 minutes). Slice bananas in 1/2, then lengthwise. Arrange on large platter. Pour cooled sauce over bananas. Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: hearty chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine potatoes, half the cheese and half the onions; mix thoroughly.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, spreading across bottom and up sides to form a shell.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, mixed vegetables, soup, milk and seasonings; pour into potato shell. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken breasts gourmet
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse in cold water and drain.
Add cucumber, tomato, celery, olives and bell pepper.
Pour 1 small sized bottle of Italian dressing over other ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/4 bottle of Salad Supreme over mixture and toss.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.
Delicious!

title: london broil marinade
directions: Marinate meat for at least one hour.

title: black forest cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda, cinnamon and cocoa.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, combine applesauce, honey, egg whites and vanilla.
Gently stir into flour mixture and mix until just blended.

title: mom's mexican rice
directions: Heat oil on high in large skillet.
Add rice and toast it. Keep stirring until toasted, then add onion and green pepper.
Keep stirring.
Add spices, then mix in tomatoes and water.
Cover, but not all the way.
Keep it on high all the time; let it boil until all the water is absorbed.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick the water, sugar and corn starch.
Stir in gelatin; cool.
Add strawberries and pour into baked pie shell; chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: panoramic easter egg(great project with kids!)
directions: Mix sugar and unbeaten egg white until thoroughly blended (consistency of wet sand).
Wash plastic egg mold (large size that is divided lengthwise); dry carefully and dust with cornstarch to be sure it's completely dry.
Fill both halves of mold with sugar mixture and unmold gently onto breadboard.
Let dry until it is firm enough to handle, about 2 to 3 hours.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Place a layer of apples, then bread crumbs and half of sugar in a greased baking pan.
Repeat and sprinkle cinnamon over top. Add 1/4 cup hot water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and brown.
Serve with whipped cream or any desired topping.
President Lincoln liked this.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into frozen pie crust. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cube bread and fry in butter until browned.
Set aside. Hard boil eggs.	Set aside.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and Roquefort cheese.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.

title: crab balls
directions: In mixing bowl, add salad dressing, mustard, eggs and spice. Add oil to skillet on medium heat.
Then add crabmeat and bread crumbs to mixing bowl and fold until well mixed.
With wet hands, shape mixture into balls and cook until golden brown.
Makes approximately 20 crab balls.

title: elena's carrot cake(easy and delicious)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the carrots, flour, sugar, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, oil and eggs.
Last, mix in the pecans, if desired.
Cook for 1/2 hour to 40 minutes.
Cool; may dust with powdered sugar if desired.

title: cabbage stew
directions: In large pot, cook meat until lightly brown.
Then add celery, onion and pepper and cook until meat is brown.
Drain.
Put in beans, corn, tomatoes, chili powder and water.
Cook for 35 minutes.
Add cabbage for the last 20 minutes of cooking.

title: potato-cheddar chowder
directions: Saute diced green pepper and onion in large pan.
Add diced potatoes and cut up broccoli and cauliflower and barely enough water to cook until vegetables are done.
Add 2 cups of milk to cooked mixture.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups grated cheese (any kind). Thicken with 2 teaspoons cornstarch and water mixture if needed.

title: lobster corn chowder
directions: Thaw lobster tails.
With scissors, remove underside membrane. Pull out meat in one piece and cut into crosswise slices.
Heat butter and saute onion, celery and mushrooms until tender but not brown.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until soup thickens slightly.
Add corn and lobster tail pieces.
Season to taste with salt, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Cook over low heat until lobster pieces are white and opaque.
Sprinkle with paprika at serving time.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Place water in a stockpot about halfway full. Bring to a boil. Remove the skin from the chicken quarters and separate, if desired. Add lemon pepper seasoning. Bring to a continuous boil. Boil until all the water is out of the pot, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together; add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add all other ingredients and fold together.
Pour into serving dish and decorate with cherries, pecans and marshmallows.
Let set for 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: apple-raisin bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl, whisk the eggs, sugar, brown sugar and milk until evenly blended.
Add bread cubes and apple and mix with a large spoon. Cover and refrigerate 40 minutes.

title: pineapple-pistachio mold
directions: Mix pineapple with its juices in pudding mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Chill 3 hours or overnight before serving.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Cook first four ingredients in 1/2 cup water.
Cook until soft ball forms in water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pecans. Stir together and pour on waxed paper.
Separate fast.

title: magic carpets(micro magic)
directions: Combine orange juice, cornstarch, honey and cinnamon stick in a 4-cup micro-safe bowl and microwave on High, uncovered, 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes, stirring once, until it boils.
Pour into 8-inch round micro-safe serving dish and remove cinnamon stick.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl except chicken.
Stir with fork until blended; transfer to a plastic bag.
Moisten chicken with water.
Shake a few pieces at a time.
Place coated pieces, skin side up, on a nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes (until golden brown).

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar and heat only enough to dissolve sugar. Mix the rest of the ingredients together and add to the first mixture.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake well before using.

title: sweet glazed carrots
directions: Blend French dressing and brown sugar in a 12-inch skillet. Heat until mixture bubbles.
Add carrots and cook, stirring constantly until glazed, about 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon meringue pie(lo-cal)
directions: Combine the water and gelatin and let stand for 5 minutes. Stir 2 tablespoons sugar in.
Cook and stir until melted.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add this to a mixture of the pumpkin, brown sugar and spice.
Freeze 15 minutes or until slightly thick, stirring occasionally.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks. Add 2 tablespoons sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in partially set pumpkin.
Mix up Dream Whip.
Reserve 1/2 cup for garnish. Fold rest into pumpkin.
Cover and chill, then spoon into cooled meringue shell.
Chill until set, then serve with garnish.

title: jello cake delight
directions: Mix jello as directed on box.
Place in refrigerator and let jell slightly.
Mix in strawberries.
Break cake in bite size pieces.
Place in a large bowl.
Pour jello and berries over cake. Put in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given, beating in eggs one at a time.
Add 1 cup hot water and mix.
Pour into 3 small or 2 medium greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes for small, 40 minutes for medium.

title: scallops a la provencale
directions: Heat peanut oil in 9-inch skillet over medium heat. Add scallops, onions, garlic, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until scallops are done, about 5 minutes. Combine sherry and cornstarch. Add to scallop mixture and cook until thickened.
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan cake
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and butter; mix until crumbly Reserve 1 cup mixture for topping.
Stir sour cream, egg, nutmeg and soda into remaining crumb mixture, just until moistened. Spread into greased oblong glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture and pecans. Microwave on High for 5 minutes; rotate dish.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool thoroughly.

title: rhubarb and orange sauce
directions: Cook rhubarb sauce with sugar added.
Add oranges and rind and tapioca last 10 to 15 minutes and continue cooking on low heat. Cool.
Pack and freeze.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Beat eggs. Add sugar and beat well; add oil, dry ingredients, vanilla and squash.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Put cloves and spice in a thin cloth.
Cook with sugar and vinegar for 10 minutes or until thickened.
Add peaches.
Cook until tender.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, remove spices.
Drain syrup from peaches and boil until thickened.
Pack syrup over peaches, filling jars to top.
Seal tightly.

title: baked cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together. Beat eggs; add milk and oil.
Combine with dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in an 8-inch pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: calico salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in refrigerator overnight to allow flavors to consolidate.

title: red velvet cake ii
directions: Mix the cake mix like the box says, except use buttermilk instead of water. In a small bowl, mix the little fudge packet with the food coloring. Beat that in with the cake mix. Stir together the baking soda and vinegar. With a spatula, fold into cake mix. Bake just like the box says.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Chill in refrigerator.

title: ladies luncheon chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice in small bowl.
Drain grapes and pineapple.
Combine chicken, celery, grapes, almonds and pineapple in large bowl.
Add mayonnaise mixture and mix well.
Chill several hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.
Serve with salad greens.

title: caramel cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Punch holes in cake with knife while cake is hot and pour condensed milk over cake, filling holes.
Pour topping over cake as well.
Chill cake, then ice with Cool Whip.
Grate or crumble candy bars and sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.
Keep cake refrigerated.

title: sausage pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a heavy frying pan, crumble sausage meat with a fork.
Saute thoroughly.
Drain fat from pan; remove sausage meat and set aside.
In another frying pan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add milk and heat until steam rises, but do not boil.
Cut cream cheese into small pieces; add to hot milk and onion mixture and let soften off the stove.
Beat eggs, then add shredded Cheddar cheese, milk mixture and seasonings.
Beat to mix thoroughly and pour into pie shell.
Top with cooked sausage. Bake 30 minutes or until set.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Make three holes.
In first hole put melted margarine, in second hole put vinegar and in third hole put vanilla.
Pour cold water over the mixture.
Mix with a fork until smooth.
Bake in a greased and floured 8-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Roll on well floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters and sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: hot tuna sandwiches
directions: Mix above with 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Put between a bun and heat in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cover pan with foil so buns won't burn.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook the ground beef and onion together. Drain.
Mix all ingredients. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot; cover and cook for 1 hour on high, then cook on low for 4 to 8 hours.

title: breast of chicken and rice
directions: Blend soup, milk and dry onion soup mix.
Stir in rice and mushrooms.
Place in greased baking dish.
Tear chicken into pieces and place on top of mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: curry green tomato chops
directions: In
a
skillet
brown
salted
and peppered pork chops. Place them
in
the
bottom
of a baking dish.
Then layer the tomatoes and the onion until it's gone.
Sprinkle on the curry powder, salt and pepper and a
spoon or two of cooking sherry. Bake at 375° for a little less than an hour.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in size.
Grease muffin pans.
Punch down dough, turn on pastry sheet and press dough flat.
Cut with cutter or shape into clover leaves.
Place in muffin tins.
Let rise again, then brush with melted butter.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 18 rolls.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and packed brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Stir in oats, coconut and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Let stand on cookie sheet until firm. Cool on rack.

title: festive holiday punch
directions: Pour apple and cranberry juices into punch bowl. Fifteen minutes before serving, add apple slices, cranberries, 7-Up and ice. Do not stir. Makes 24 servings.

title: sweet potato dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with fresh vegetables or favorite chips.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Whisk all together well and coat 1 pound of pecans.
Place in a single layer on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°. Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients into a big bowl and mix with clean hands; add a pinch of salt.
After well mixed, pat the dough on a buttered cookie pan (about 1/4-inch thick).
Brush top with pastry brush dipped in water.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.
Press nuts into dough.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown. Cut into shapes while warm.
Let cookies cool about 10 minutes before removing them with a spatula.

title: taco dip
directions: Save part of the cheese for top.
Mix all together.
Sprinkle on cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with chips.

title: quick chile salsa
directions: Chop chiles into small pieces.
Combine chiles and tomatoes in a jar, mashing tomatoes well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shake well.
Cover jar.
Let stand overnight.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 350° for 40 minutes.
If recipe is doubled allow more baking time.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Cook chicken in oil 2 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook until tender, about 4 minutes, stirring frequently. Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add chicken broth from skillet to liquid to equal 1 1/2 cups.
Add liquid to skillet; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and reserved tomatoes.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with vegetable dippers.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In top of double boiler, over hot (not boiling) water, combine chocolate and 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Heat until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; set aside.
In small bowl combine graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted butter; mix well.
Pat firmly into 9-inch spring-form pan, covering bottom and 1/2 inch up sides; set aside.
In large bowl beat cream cheese until light and creamy. Gradually beat in remaining 3/4 cup sugar.
Mix in sour cream and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Divide batter in half.
Stir melted chocolate mixture into first half.
Pour into crumb lined pan; cover with plain batter.
With a knife, swirl plain batter with chocolate batter to marbleize.
Bake about 50 minutes or until only center of cheesecake will shake.
Cool on wire rack; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place foil over for last 3 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.

title: chicken wings teriyaki(barbecue)
directions: To prepare Teriyaki Sauce, combine all ingredients in saucepan and heat.
Simmer until cornstarch is cooked.
Watch and stir constantly.
Add 1/4 cup white wine after sauce has cooled. Set aside.

title: icebox pie for diabetics
directions: Beat eggs and Sweet 'N Low. Add fruit juice. Cook until slightly thickened.
Add jello. Cool.
Whip chilled milk with a little lemon juice.
Add egg mixture to whipped milk. Put into graham cracker crust.
You can top with Cool Whip.
Put in icebox until firm.

title: toodie's hamburger surprise
directions: Form meat into patties. Place into skillet and cook first side brown. Turn patties over and cook second side light brown. Remove patties from skillet and pour off excess grease. Place patties back into skillet light side down. Put in all vegetables starting with vegetable taking the longest time to cook. Put water in filling skillet at least halfway up on vegetables. Salt and pepper to taste. Place the butter or margarine around on top of vegetables. Cook, covered, until all vegetables are tender. Should make enough for 4 adults. Enjoy.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Process until well blended.

title: apricot torte
directions: Crush biscuits to fine crumbs.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar and butter.
Pat about 2/3 of crumbs on bottom of greased 8-inch round cake pan.
Arrange apricot halves on crumb layer.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice using package directions.
Saute onion and celery in butter in skillet until tender.
Mix broccoli and rice in a bowl. Add soup, water and Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Stir in sauteed vegetables.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon honey
directions: Grate rind of lemons and squeeze out juice. Beat eggs lightly. Place all ingredients into top part of double boiler and cook over boiling water, stirring until thick.
Pour into hot jars and seal with vacuum seals or preserving wax.
May be stored in refrigerator for several weeks, if unsealed.
Mandarin orange or grapefruit honey can be made in the same way.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, milk and onion soup mix.
Put mixture into an ungreased, shallow baking pan.
Wet hands and shape into a loaf. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
May double recipe.

title: julie's barbecued spareribs
directions: Mix brown sugar, chili powder, salt and paprika together.
Rub on ribs and baste with mixture of tomato sauce and vinegar.
Bake slowly until tender.

title: zucchini with chives
directions: Wash and trim zucchini.
Cut into slices, about 1/2-inch thick.
Drop them into a saucepan containing a little boiling, salted water and cook until soft.
Stir over a gentle heat to dry out.
Add sour cream.
Stir until well mixed and heated.
Add chopped chives and serve.

title: calvin krispies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, marshmallows, margarine and peanut butter in a large bowl in microwave, stirring every 30 seconds. Dump in the cereal and mix thoroughly.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Harden briefly.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pilgrim pie
directions: Chill pie shell.
In a medium saucepan combine and heat pumpkin for 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar, salt and spices.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add cream and rum.
Stir into pumpkin mixture.
Strain through a fine strainer and pour into chilled unbaked shell.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes.
If necessary, cover edges with strips of foil to keep from browning too rapidly.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 to 40 minutes more or until set.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until thoroughly mixed.
Add buttermilk and yeast that has been dissolved in warm water.
Work together until mixed well.
Cover bowl and refrigerate until ready to use.
Roll 1/2-inch thick on floured board.
Cut and dip in melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 400° or 425°, depending on your oven.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: western baked beans
directions: Mix pork and beans with brown sugar and catsup.
Brown in skillet the beef, onion, green pepper and salt.
Add the bean mix and pour into casserole dish.
Bake about 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: ham & cheddar breakfast casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in a 10x6 inch baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: texas hot hash
directions: Combine beef, onion, green pepper and garlic in a large skillet.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: cherry creme pie
directions: Combine condensed milk with 1/3 cup lemon juice, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix well.
Fold in 1/2 cup whipped cream.
Put in baked pie shell.
Pour cherry pie filling over it.
Chill.

title: crock pot chilli
directions: Brown meat, onions and green peppers until done.
Add all other ingredients in a crock pot; add the ground beef.
Cook on high for 1 to 2 hours or on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter.
Mix well. Gradually add sugars; cream thoroughly.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Sift together flour and baking soda; blend in with peanut butter mixture.

title: spicy rice and vegetables
directions: Saute vegetables in butter and honey.
Add rice and continue to saute until onions are clear.
Add water and boil 5 minutes. Turn heat to low; let rice absorb water, about 35 minutes.
In last 5 minutes of cooking, add apple and almonds.
Serves 4.

title: potato bread
directions: Scald milk. Add sugar, butter, salt and mashed potatoes. cool to lukewarm. meanwhile, dissolve yeast in water. Add to cooled milk mixture. Add whole wheat flour and 1 c. white flour. Beat 2 minutes with mixer. Stir in 6-7 more coups flour until dough leaves sides of bowl. Turn onto lightly floured surface. Knead gently until dough forms a smooth ball. Place in greased bowl. Turn once to grease top of dough. Cover and let rise in a warm place away from drafts until doubled. 1 1/2 - 2 hours. Punch down and let rise again until double. Turn onto floured surface and divide dough into 3 equal parts. Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Form into 3 loaves and place in greased bread pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes. Remove from pans and place on rack to cool.

title: mango bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix together and let stand in bowl about 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch or 2 x 2-inch pan or for 1 hour in loaf pan.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine as directed on package. Drain linguine and add dressing and Salad Supreme to taste. Stir thoroughly and the refrigerate overnight. Before serving stir in veggies, meat and cheeses.

title: luncheon pan rolls
directions: Scald milk and butter. Add sugar and salt. Let stand until lukewarm. Add eggs, yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Continue beating, adding flour until dough is stiff enough to handle. Let rise until double in size (takes about 2 hours). Then knead gently for 1 minute. Shape into balls and place in buttered pan, placing them so they touch lightly. Let rolls rise until they are double in size. Then bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown, about 20 minutes. Serve hot. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: boston baked beans in crock-pot
directions: Wash beans, mix everything in a slow cooker and put on

lid. Turn to high until contents are bubbling, then turn to low and cook 14-16 hours or longer. Turn the cooker to high once or twice if beans do not seem to be cooking. They are done when they have turned a nice dark reddish brown. Correct seasoning.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes; when done, cut in half.
Scoop out insides and mash with margarine and milk until smooth.
Fill in potato skins and top with cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Brown and drain beef and sausage.
In large bowl, mix ground beef, sausage, onion, chilli peppers, picante sauce, cheese and beans.
Take your loaves of bread and scoop out the middle.
Fill with meat mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Makes two loaves.
Slice when cool.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, combine pineapple with its juice and sugar. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and syrupy, about 20 minutes.
When cake is done, pierce top with fork at 1-inch intervals.
Pour on pineapple mixture. Cool completely.
In medium bowl, beat cream until soft peaks form. Add confectioners sugar and vanilla. Continue beating until stiff.
Spread over cake. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 16 servings.
Contains 420 calories each.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg and milk together; add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour 1/2 cup servings into funnel.
Let drip in swirls to form 4-inch diameter circle in hot oil.
Turn after 1 minute.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 6 to 8 cakes.

title: crock-pot special
directions: Slice potatoes and layer in crock-pot.
Add sliced onions, carrots and celery.
Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add garlic powder, if desired.
Pour meat over vegetables in crock-pot.
Pour tomato soup and 1 can of water on top.
Cover and cook on low for
7 to 8 hours.
Stir and serve.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg with hand beater until fluffy; beat in remaining ingredients just until smooth.
Grease heated griddle.

title: spicy bread pudding
directions: Butter, sugar and cinnamon four slices of bread and toast. Cut each piece of toasted bread into 9 pieces and place in shallow pan.
Mix the eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Pour over bread pieces.
Add nutmeg and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rice-a-roni porcupines
directions: Combine Rice-a-Roni with ground beef and egg.
Shape into meatballs (approximately 20).
