Brown on all sides in skillet. Combine beef seasoning packet with hot water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes; thicken gravy if desired.

title: layer green salad
directions: Add the ingredients as listed in layers.
Chill before serving.

title: potato wedges
directions: Put ingredients in a bag and shake.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in large pan.
Put the potatoes in the margarine.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then turn the potatoes and bake 20 more minutes or until done.

title: scalloped potato-hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in saucepan.
(Pour off excess fat.)
Season to taste.
Add tomato soup.
Pour meat mixture into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Arrange sliced potatoes on top of meat mixture.
Pour milk into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix milk and lemonade juice.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.

title: three-ring punch
directions: Combine the juices before the ginger ale.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: prune macaroons
directions: Mix and shape into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 60.

title: seafood fettuccine
directions: In large saucepan, saut in butter the shrimp, mushrooms, garlic powder, salt and pepper for 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in fettuccine, Parmesan cheese, milk and sour cream. Cook over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes until heated through (do not boil). Serve.

title: marinated eye of round
directions: Spread meat tenderizer on meat (both sides); let sit for 30 minutes.
Mix together last 5 ingredients and spread on meat (all sides).
Marinate 4 to 4 1/2 hours, turning every hour.
Cook at 475° for 15 minutes; turn oven down to 275° and cook 45 minutes more.
Slice meat to serve.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix together in casserole.
Pour over it 1/4 pound melted oleo.
Add milk to fill half the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered.

title: unfried chicken(yields 4 servings)
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of vegetable oil.
Remove all skin from chicken.
Put chicken in a large bowl with ice water.
Toss all breading ingredients into a large, tightly sealing plastic bag.
Seal and shake well to mix. Remove 2 pieces of chicken from the ice water.
Roll each piece in the yogurt.
Put the chicken into the plastic bag; reseal and shake to coat thoroughly.
Transfer the breaded chicken to the prepared baking sheet.
Repeat the process until all 12 pieces are breaded.
Spray chicken lightly with vegetable oil.
Place the baking sheet on the bottom shelf of the oven and bake for 1 hour, turning the pieces every 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: favorite barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the garlic.
Mix well.
Pour into jars to store.
This can stay in the refrigerator for several weeks or can be frozen.
One hour before using the sauce, add garlic.

title: lemon or orange supreme cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Before taking out of pan, pour glaze around edge of cake. Take out of pan and leave upside down. Take a knife and make openings in top of cake.
Pour remaining glaze on top of cake and in openings.

title: georgia peanut cookies
directions: Tips for extra crunchiness:
add 1/2 cup chopped unsalted peanuts to the dough after mixing in the flour.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread mixture on a small serving plate.
Top with nuts.
Serve with apple wedges.

title: red beans and rice(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Soak beans overnight, then cook beans until they are tender; drain off all the water.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown deer, onion, pepper and celery; drain.
Combine all ingredients; let simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Great served with white or yellow rice and jalapeno cornbread.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Mix pizza sauce, corn flakes, egg, pepper, sugar, onion and oregano in large mixing bowl until fully blended.
Add in ground beef and mushrooms.
Mix until fully blended.

title: rhubarb strawberry cobbler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients to make a crumble.
Spread 1/2 mixture in a baking dish-save 1/2 mixture.
Add strawberries and rhubarb.
In a saucepan; mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until it thickens.
Add vanilla.
Pour over rhubarb and strawberries.
Sprinkle on remaining crumb mix.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate several hours or overnight.
Line shallow pan with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.
Discard marinade.

title: bacardi rum-pina colada cake
directions: *With
vanilla
increase water to 3/4 cup and add 1 cup coconut to batter.

title: berliner napfkuchen(berlin chocolate ring)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 ounce fluted ring mold. Set aside.
In large bowl, beat together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Gradually add flour mixture and milk alternately to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla, lemon peel and currants.
Batter should hold its shape when mixing but should be moist enough to drop slowly off a wooden spoon.
Pour batter into greased mold. Bake 1 hour or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes in pan.
Then turn out of pan on a cooling rack.
Spoon melted chocolate over warm cake, coating completely.
Sprinkle nuts over cake.
Cool completely.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add pineapple and bread.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: On waxed paper, unroll 2 crescent rolls. Press together at seams, making a square. Spread with fingers to make thin. Spread thin layer of mustard. With fingers, spread a layer of sausage on rolls. Roll up and wrap in wax paper. Make 3 more rolls the same as before. Refrigerate. When ready to bake, slice each roll into 8 or 10 slices. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. May be reheated in oven for 5 minutes.

title: frosting
directions: Put ingredients into bowl.
Add milk, a little at a time.
Mix with hand mixer until you get desired consistency.
This frosting works very well for cake decorating and tastes great.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Pour juice from cherries into saucepan.
Mix in Jell-O and heat until dissolved.
Pour into bowl; add Coke.
Allow to partially congeal.
Add pineapple and pecans; let set overnight.

title: crispy confections
directions: Melt candy with water in saucepan over low heat.
Stir frequently until smooth.
Pour over cereal and coconut mixture; toss until well coated.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Let stand until firm.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Blend with mixer at medium speed until well mixed.
Batter will be thick.
Place thick batter in tube pan covered with shortening and flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cake should spring back when pressing.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck. Mix with soup, onion and Tater Tots. Place in casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: hannah's crispy candy
directions: Blend together 10x sugar, margarine and peanut butter.
Add coconut, graham cracker crumbs and pecans.
Mix together well. Form into eggs or ball shapes.
Coat with chocolate.
Melt Hershey milk chocolate candy bars in double boiler.
Add 1/4 cake grated paraffin.
Coat candy when chilled.

title: spiced grapes
directions: Wash a gallon of grapes and remove hulls from pulp.
Heat the pulp 10 minutes.
Then run through a sieve to remove the seeds. Put pulp and hulls in a pan.
Add sugar, cinnamon, cloves and vinegar.
Cook, stirring often until it is the consistency of preserves.
Pour into small, sterile jars and seal.
Very good served with meats.

title: "melitzanes me loukanika" - eggplant and sausage pie
directions: Dice the eggplant, leaving the skin on.
Toss with salt and drain in a colander for 1 hour.
Rinse under cold water and pat dry.
Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet and cook the sausage until it has rendered its fat.
Drain.
In the same pan, cook the diced eggplant; add another tablespoon of olive oil and toss constantly.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's waldorf salad
directions: Core and cube apples.
Mix apples, walnuts, grapes and celery together.
Stir in condensed milk.
Mix Miracle Whip with sugar and stir into apple mixture.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour and serve chilled.

title: julia child's potatoes
directions: Boil and peel potatoes.
When cool, cut into slices.
Grease casserole dish with margarine.
Cover with layer of potatoes, then white sauce and 2/3 cup Swiss cheese.

title: 4 layer chocolate pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar together and fold in 1 cup of Cool Whip. Spread this on cooled crust.
Make pudding according to package directions except use 1/2 cup less milk than called for.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over chocolate layer.
May grate chocolate to sprinkle on top.
Makes 20 to 24 squares.

title: microwave beef goulash
directions: Crumble ground beef into 3 quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High 8 to 9 minutes.
Break up and stir after 4 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and microwave 10 minutes.
Stir.
Cover and microwave 10 to 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes until macaroni is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: low-fat crab dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasoning. Mix well, then stir in Cheddar cheese and crab.
Cover and chill two hours.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers, bread sticks or vegetables.
Yields approximately 20 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute onions and celery in bacon drippings until tender. Combine sugar and flour; add to skillet with vinegar, water, salt and mustard. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.

title: burgundy mushroom meat loaf
directions: Combine ketchup and red wine.
Set aside.
Reserve 2 tablespoons mushrooms; set aside.
Finely chop remaining mushrooms; set aside.
Combine chuck, oats, chopped mushrooms, 1/4 cup ketchup mixture, egg, mustard, garlic salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf.
Place in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray.
Pour remaining ketchup mixture over chuck.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 65 minutes.
Top with reserved mushrooms. Continue to bake an additional 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: italian rice with mushrooms
directions: In a large skillet, cook rice, tomatoes, mushrooms and onion in butter for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add broth, wine and seasonings.
Cover; simmer for 45 minutes, or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in peas.
Add cheese.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Mix
graham
cracker
crumbs,
margarine, confectioners sugar and peanut butter together in a bowl.
Roll mixture into walnut size balls.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter and peanut butter together.
Roll into balls and chill.
Melt wax and chocolate chips on top of stove in a double boiler.
Dip chilled balls into melted chocolate with toothpicks.
Drop on waxed paper until hardened.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out.
Cut out with cookie cutter. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in 2-quart bowl.
Pour mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set dish in a shallow pan, holding 1-inch of hot water.
Bake 45 minutes, or until pudding is firm at edges.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 6.

title: smoked turkey log
directions: Mash up with hands and form into ball or log. Roll (or press on top and sides) in 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 2 tablespoons chopped parsley. (Easier to roll in pecans or form into some special shape if chilled in fridge first.) Serve with crackers of your choice (Ritz, Sociables, Keebler, Wheat Thins, etc.).

title: state fair blackberry pie
directions: Thaw berries, drain, and reserve juice.
Mix juice with dry ingredients; cook until thickened and clear.
Add berries, lemon juice, butter.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked shell.
Seal top crust and cut steam vents.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and make 30 minutes more or until crust is golden brown.

title: orange baked yams
directions: Place yams in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Mix orange juice, brown sugar and cinnamon in a separate bowl.
Pour over yams.
Drizzle melted butter over yams and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 10 to 15 minutes until yams are hot and top is slightly caramelized.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Cream butter until real soft; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Sift all dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add bananas and pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Use 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Cook noodles in
quarts salted water for 17 minutes, then drain.

title: pie crust
directions: Melt oleo. Add to flour and milk. Roll out between wax paper. Makes 9 in crust.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Follow directions on box for mixing cookie dough; divide and roll into 36 equally sized balls.
Place each one in cup of the muffin tin.
Do not grease tin or pat down dough.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: crusty chicken casserole
directions: Bone chicken and cut meat into bite-sized pieces. Arrange in a well-greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and poultry seasoning. Is a separate bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add milk and butter; mix well. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the egg mixture. Mix until well blended; pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes, until golden brown and puffy.

title: asparagus medley
directions: Cut
asparagus	diagonally.
Steam
until tender-crisp. Thinly slice
mushrooms
and
red
onion.
Cut
tomatoes into wedges. About
1/2 hour before serving add the Italian dressing.
Toss lightly to blend ingredients.
(If asparagus is not available substitute broccoli or fresh green beans.) This is a great summer salad!

title: regas restaurant's famous blueberry muffins
directions: Beat together sugar and oil with electric mixer. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add flour (unsifted), salt and baking powder. Mix well. Stir in milk. Pour into flour-dusted and greased muffin pans. Sprinkle blueberries on top of each muffin; press them in lightly. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 24 to 36 muffins.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix in very large bowl and spoon by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 minutes at 375°.

title: potato bean salad
directions: Toss potatoes, pickles and onions together in a large bowl. Mix beans with mayonnaise or salad dressing and pour over potato mixture.
Toss gently until all ingredients are well blended. Taste for seasoning and add salt, if necessary.
Chill well; overnight if desired.
Before serving, garnish with pickles or chopped parsley.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High 4 minutes or until melted, stirring after 2 minutes. Stir in sour cream. Microwave 1 minute. Serve hot with tortilla chips or cut up vegetables. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: florentine macaroni bake
directions: Prepare dinner as directed, omitting margarine. Add cream cheese, stirring over low heat until melted. Add spinach, eggs (beaten), bacon, salt and pepper. Pour into 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick punch
directions: Scoop lime sherbet into bowl (punch bowl).
Pour the 7-Up or ginger ale over the sherbet (becomes frothy).
Makes 12 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Place bite size pieces of lettuce in bottom of flat baking dish.
Sprinkle peas over lettuce.
Sprinkle celery and onion over mixture.
Crumble crisp cooked bacon over mixture.
Add slices of boiled eggs.
Mix 2 c. of mayonnaise (I use salad dressing) with a little sugar and spread over mixture.
Spread cheddar cheese over top.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: pigs-n-blanket
directions: Wrap sausage with 1/2 biscuit.
Cheese can also be wrapped around sausage prior to bread (optional).
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Mix fruit with brown sugar in baking pan and set aside.
Mix flour, white sugar, salt and cinnamon and set aside.
Beat egg. Mix with flour mixture and spread over fruit.
Pour butter over top.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Use 3-quart baking dish and square dish.
Place chicken parts in baking dishes.
Cover with mixture of soups, water, rice, margarine, salt and pepper.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Makes a lot.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Melt chocolate with milk.
Stir in sugar (reserving 1/2 cup sugar) until well blended.
Add nuts.
If mixture is dry and hard to handle, add 1 to 2 tablespoons of milk.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Sprinkle with reserved sugar.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen Snowballs.

title: taco pie
directions: Spray 9 x 11 inch pan with non-stick spray. Press rolls into pan. Mix ground round, onions, peppers and saute. Add tomato paste, water and taco seasoning. Mix well, put 1/2 of meat mixture on crust, sprinkle with 1/2 cheese. Add remaining meat and top with remaining cheese. bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: fudge
directions: Put all ingredients into boiler; cook until it thickens.
Beat until it is very hard and firm, then pour into buttered dish. Cool; cut into squares.

title: chinese chews
directions: Preheat oven
to
Sift
dry
ingredients (except powdered sugar) together;
add pecans and dates, stirring well until each piece
is
well coated with beaten eggs.
Spread in thin layer in
long
(greased) pan.
Bake only until edges are stiff enough to
hold
shape.
Cut	into
small
squares.
Use powdered sugar to coat each square and work into a ball.
Roll in additional powdered sugar.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt 1 cup of sugar in iron skillet or heavy saucepan until caramelized.
Mix remaining 2 cups sugar with milk, butter and salt and cook slowly.
When it begins to boil, add the caramelized sugar and stir well.
Let come to a good boil.
Cook slowly to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Beat and add nuts.
Spread pineapple on cake while hot.
This icing can be used on any of your favorite cake recipes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together 10 minutes; cool.
Add grape juice, lemon and orange juice and pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice.
Serves about 25 people.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries.
Heat and dissolve jello.
Let cool and add Coca-Cola.
Put in refrigerator.
When jello begins to thicken, add chopped nuts, chopped cherries and cream cheese.
Return to refrigerator and let it finish jelling.

title: onion cornbread
directions: Melt butter, add onion and saute until tender, about 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add sour cream, salt and 1/2 cup cheese to onion; set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the butter.
Pour mixture into an 8 1/2 x 12-inch Pyrex casserole dish.
Pour melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, or until browned on top.

title: mincemeat refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add vanilla and egg.
Mix.
Add dry ingredients with mincemeat and nuts.
Shape into roll.
Store in refrigerator.
Slice.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend ingredients like a cake. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan. Add apples and nuts last. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place points toward the center on a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press bottom and sides to form crust, sealing perforations.

title: old mcdonald's favorite dip
directions: Shred cheeses.
Chop spring onions.
Spray a 12 x 8-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine beans and taco seasoning mix.
Spoon into baking dish.
Sprinkle onions on top of bean mixture.
Spread sour cream on top of beans and onions. Sprinkle cheeses on top of sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: deviled hamburger(serves 8)
directions: Combine and shape into patties.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Stir altogether.
Cook until hard ball at 265°.
Pour over popcorn and form balls.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: honey-banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease (not oil) bottom only of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, blend honey, bananas and margarine. Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in remaining ingredients, just until moistened.
Pour in prepared pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix, then add nuts and dates.
Bake about 75 minutes at 350°. Cool in pans, then remove.
Be sure to grease pans.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: cauliflower-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions.
Drain well.
Add cream of celery soup, Cheddar cheese soup, salt and pepper.
Pour into large casserole. Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour or until bubbling.
If desired, crushed corn flakes may be added to top of casserole before baking.
Makes approximately 15 servings.

title: excellent tortilla soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain. Add chopped onion and cook until tender. Add other ingredients through chicken broth, and simmer until hot and seasonings blended.

title: meringue surprises
directions: Combine egg whites, vanilla and salt.
Beat until stiff, but not dry.
Beat in sugar gradually until stiff and satiny.
Divide mixture into equal portions.
Add red and green food coloring. Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet. Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: 4 layer pudding cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix together margarine and flour and press into bottom of 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Bake in tube pan 2 hours at 300°.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Set aside 1/3 of it.
To the 2/3 add all the other ingredients.
Fill tortillas; roll seam-side down and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dilute 1/3 mixture to soup with milk and pour over the enchiladas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well before baking.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini-egg casserole
directions: Saute onion and zucchini.
Place in bottom of 9-inch casserole.
In separate bowl, mix together egg and grated Parmesan cheese.
Pour on top of zucchini.
Add tomato sauce.
Top with shredded Mozzarella.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: german salad
directions: Shred cabbage, bell peppers and onions.
Toss well.
Bring sugar, vinegar, salt, honey and salad oil to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture while hot.
Let cool and do not stir.
When cool, refrigerate.
This will keep up to 6 weeks.

title: ham-potato chowder
directions: Melt butter in large kettle.
Add onion, celery, garlic salt and ham.
Cook until onion and celery are tender, but not browned. Add potatoes, salt, chili powder and water.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and tomatoes.
Heat, but do not boil.
A little less milk might be preferred.
Serves 6.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, drain well.
Set aside.
Place bread cubes in 13 x 9-inch greased dish.
Top bread cubes with sausage and cheese.
Combine 2 cups milk and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl and pour over bread mixture.
Cover and chill 8 hours. Combine soup with remaining 1/2 cup milk and pour over casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and cherries.
In a large bowl, mix fruit, cherries, marshmallows, coconut and sour cream. Mix well and chill before serving.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and onions; drain the grease.
Add the other ingredients with the exception of the cabbage and macaroni. Cook for 20 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Cool with cold water.
Toss all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt marshmallows with butter.
Boil milk with sugar for 6 minutes. Pour over marshmallows and chocolate pieces.
Stir until creamy and thick.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.

title: chicken-broccoli delight
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and add soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and mix.
Melt remaining 1/2 cup margarine and mix with bread crumbs.
Place alternate layers of chicken, broccoli and stuffing mix with soup mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or large casserole dish, ending with soup mixture.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, and spices.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, buttermilk and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and butter.
Beat until well blended.
Bake in 350 oven.

title: hot winter punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Brew for 30 minutes.
Add spices; brew for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 gallon.
Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: cheesy hash brown potatoes
directions: Cut a small slit in bag of potatoes and defrost in microwave for 3 minutes.

title: beef in casserole
directions: Cook beef and drain fat.
Saute onion.
Add salt, sugar, tomato sauce, tomatoes, garlic and pepper.
Simmer meat sauce 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and cream cheese to cooked macaroni. Alternate layers of meat sauce, macaroni mixture and grated cheese in greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: quick and easy brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in cocoa and sugar.
Turn off heat and add eggs (one at a time), beating well with wire whisk after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Add flour, stirring until blended.
Turn into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Top with pecans.
Heat oven to 350°. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Pour hot mixture over carrot mixture.
Cover and marinate 12 hours in refrigerator.
Lasts 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: sister's kraut salad
directions: Mash and drain kraut; boil other ingredients for 5 minutes. Mix with kraut and chill.
Can be stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Cut in margarine.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat egg.
Add milk and yeast to water mixture.
Add egg/milk/yeast mixture to flour mixture and beat well.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough in rectangular shape to 1/2-inch thickness on floured board. Brush with melted margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Roll up dough along long edge.
Cut with thread into 1-inch thick slices.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg and milk; stir in oil.
Sift and add baking powder, salt and flour.
Stir just until moistened.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Cook in muffin
pans for 20 to 25 minutes at 400° (preheated).

title: rolls
directions: Mix all, then add flour. Knead dough until it is not sticky. Make rolls and let rise. Butter pan and tops of rolls. Cook at 400° until brown.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda in large mixing bowl.
Soak apricots in hot water to plump and tenderize.
Mix eggs, buttermilk, apricot nectar and melted oleo; add to dry ingredients and mix.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake an hour to 75 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: beef enchilada pie
directions: Cook ground beef, garlic, onion and chili powder in frying pan over medium heat until browned. Add beans and chilies. Preheat oven to 350°. Mix 1/2 cup of soup (do not add water) with stewed tomatoes.

title: nut and cracker snack
directions: Mix peanuts and Ritz.
Mix remaining ingredients, bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over peanuts and Ritz mixture. Mix well.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: ham slices with rice stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In 8-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot butter or margarine, cook onions and celery until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in rice and poultry seasoning.
Slash edges of ham to prevent curling. On rack in open roasting pan, place 1 ham slice
and top with rice mixture.
Place second ham slice over stuffing.
Secure with toothpicks.
Bake stuffed ham slices 1 1/4 hours or until heated through.
Mix in cup corn syrup and sherry. During last 15 minutes of baking time, brush mixture over ham.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium mixing bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Stir again prior to serving.
Serve chilled with tortilla chips or vegetables.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/3 cup of butter in a 9-inch square cake pan in the oven and remove from heat.
Stir in the brown sugar; sprinkle the chopped pecans evenly over the sugar mixture.
Arrange pineapple slices on top of the sugar, and put a cherry inside of each pineapple ring.
Set aside.
In a small bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: cherry squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to butter in large bowl, creaming at medium speed until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour gradually.
Pour into well-greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Mark off 20 squares.
Spoon filling onto each square.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar or serve with Cool Whip.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and place in casserole dish.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put corn into 2 brown paper grocery bags (1 inside the other). Boil together in microwave for 2 minutes the brown sugar, Karo syrup and margarine.
Remove from microwave.
Stir in baking soda. Pour over popped corn.
Mix well.
Fold open ends of bags over. Microwave on High 4 1/2 minutes, removing after 1 minute each time and shaking well.
Pour out onto waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Prepare white cake mix, adding 3 tablespoons creme de menthe. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to cake directions.
Cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cornflake crumbs) and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish and spread with cornflake crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
May be prepared and frozen.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl with a lid and a good seal. Shake until it forms a ball (will be sticky).
Makes two 9-inch pie shells or one 9 x 13-inch.
Press out in pie pans or cobbler pan.
Prick with fork for pie shells. Bake at 400° until golden brown, or, bake as pie filling directs.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and salt together; add mayonnaise and 1/2 cup
water and mix well.
Add vanilla, cocoa and remainder of water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Pat into 6 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool, slice and sprinkle or roll in additional 10x sugar.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients.
Chill for a few hours.

title: spiced tea
directions: Dissolve sugar in some of the water or juice.
Put tea bags and spices in basket of urn coffee maker.
Brew.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine in large mixer bowl, flour, baking powder, salt, pudding mix, margarine, egg and milk. Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into 9 or 10 inch well greased baking pan. Place well drained peaches over the batter. In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and 3 tablespoons of the juice. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Spoon cream cheese mixture to within 1 inch of edge of the batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and combine with remaining ingredients. Mash together with fork until mixed thoroughly.
Pour mixture into glass baking dish; bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: rice and pork casserole
directions: Cut pork into little pieces.
Salt and pepper the meat and saute it in skillet with about 1 to 2 tablespoons oil; drain. Place meat into a casserole dish.
Top it with carrots, onions, tomato sauce and chicken broth.
Boil it for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add rice and let it come to a boil.
Place the covered casserole into an oven and bake it for 50 minutes at 375°.
Serve with mustard.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese with beef
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
In 12-inch skillet, over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in ground beef.
Over medium-high heat, cook until pan juices evaporate and meat is browned.
Spoon off fat, if any. Stir in tomato sauce and 3/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer 25 minutes to blend flavors.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Roll out biscuits as flat as you can.
Put applesauce in center, then fold over and pinch together.
Bring to a boil the 7-Up, sugar, margarine and spice.
Pour over turnovers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: christmas holly
directions: Melt oleo.
Add marshmallows and mix well.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Stir well.
Add cornflakes.
When cornflakes are well coated, drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Drop 3 cinnamon candies on each cluster.
Flakes assume shape of holly leaves. Very pretty!

title: chicken divan
directions: In a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish, place a layer of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry and spread on top of broccoli.
Place a layer of chicken on top of soup mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix bread crumbs and butter and spread on top of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Brown chops.
Place in roaster.
Combine bread cubes, celery, carrots, butter, eggs and parsley.
Spoon over pork chops.
Blend soup and water and pour over dressing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrots
directions: Place carrots in pot with salt and water.
Bring to boil; cover.
Reduce to low heat and cook until fork can be easily inserted.
Remove; drain.
Pour into serving bowl.
Pour melted butter or margarine over carrots and sprinkle with sugar.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into crusts and chill.

title: black eyed pea salad
directions: Drain first four ingredients and combine with celery and onions.
Heat sugar in oil and vinegar till melted.
Pour over salad and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain salad before serving.

title: mexican corn bread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown ground beef until crumbly, draining off any excess fat.
Add onions and jalapenos.
Combine eggs, 1 cup of corn and milk and add to corn bread mix; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour half of corn bread batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Top with beef mixture, cheese and remaining corn.
Pour onto half of corn bread batter on top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Will serve approximately 8 people.

title: vegetables au gratin
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions. Drain. In a saucepan, combine milk, cornstarch, salt and pepper. Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, then cook 2 more minutes. Stir in cheese until melted. Remove from heat. Cool and freeze.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Debone chicken thighs; remove skin and all fat.
Flatten by beating with meat tenderizer.
Sift flour with salt, pepper and onion or garlic powder.
Roll chicken in flour mixture.
Dip in beaten egg and roll again in flour mixture.

title: tandy cakes
directions: Heat the peanut butter.
Spread over hot cake, then refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt the milk chocolate and Crisco in a double boiler.
Spread this over the chilled peanut butter.
Chill for another hour and cut into squares to enjoy.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix butter, 1/2 cup brown
sugar
and 1 cup flour until crumbly.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about
minutes
until lightly brown.
Combine remaining ingredients well and
pour over baked mixture.
Bake again at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.
Cut in bars.

title: milkless super energy drink
directions: Put all the ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend on high speed until all ice has been chopped.
Yield: 1 or 2 servings.

title: walnuts on ritz
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar, vanilla and baking powder.
Fold in crushed Ritz crackers and nuts.
Fold with a spoon.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch greased dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Put small Cool Whip on while hot.
Cool completely.
Add large Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts on top.
Delicious!

title: rocky road fudge brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: mom's perfect cornbread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and yellow cornmeal.
Add eggs or whites, milk and oil.
Beat with mixer or by hand just until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding with crushed pineapple, stir well.
Add chunks and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.
Add bananas right before serving.
Quick, easy and excellent!

title: old-fashion pecan pie
directions: Add syrup, sugar and margarine in saucepan.
Boil gently for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly.
Place the broken pecan pieces in the pie shell.
Mix the eggs, vanilla and salt together, then slowly stir in the cooled syrup.
Pour over the pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a tester comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Serves 8.

title: irish meat loaf
directions: Blend beef and pork in a bowl.
Add next 6 ingredients; mix to blend.
Stir in apples.
Shape into loaf on jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Drain off excess fat. Combine potatoes and broccoli; frost loaf with potato mixture. Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Let stand about 5 minutes before removing to warmed platter.

title: spanish rice
directions: Put all ingredients together in double boiler and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Stir with fork several times to lift from bottom.
Fry 4 strips of bacon, put bacon fat with rice, crumble bacon and add just before serving in mounds.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie filling.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then spread pie filling on top of that.
Spread remainder of batter.
Drop by spoonfuls.
When finished baking, sprinkle with powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
May also top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until clear, but not brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until heated through. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve hot or cold.
Enjoy!

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Cut in pieces 1 stick margarine.
Place over soup mixture.
Mix flour and milk and pour over chicken.
Pour 3 cups chicken broth on top of this.
Add English peas and carrots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bourbon pecan bread
directions: Makes 2 loaves.
Soak raisins in bourbon for 30 minutes; drain, reserving bourbon.
If necessary, add more bourbon to make 1/3 cup. Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans and line pan bottoms with greased wax paper.
In bowl, cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating well.
Add flour in thirds, alternating with bourbon.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in raisins, pecans and vanilla.

In large bowl with clean beaters, beat the egg whites until soft peaks form (tips curl) when beaters are raised. Gradually beat remaining sugar in; beat until stiff peaks form. Fold about 2 cups of beaten egg whites into batter to lighten it. Then gently fold the remaining beaten egg whites into mixture. Cook 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Frost with creamed cheese frosting.

title: oven scones
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift together flour, sugar, cream of tartar and baking soda.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Slowly add milk, mixing with a fork until a soft pliable dough forms.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up and boil chicken, covered with water.
Lift chicken from broth; cool and bone, placing chicken back in broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil to get ready for the dumplings.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Spread chopped pecans in bottom of pie crust and set aside. Cream sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Add pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Let chill 2 hour.
Garnish with strawberries or pecans.

title: pork pizza snack
directions: Brown and drain ground pork.
Stir in all other ingredients and mix well.

title: white fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix sugar, flour, cream of tartar, salt and milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Boil 8 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat very vigorously with wooden spoon until very thick.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Cool.
Cut into small pieces.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Prepare cake in 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Mix pudding, milk and liqueur.
Crumble cake.
Layer cake, pudding, Cool Whip and crushed Heath bars.
Repeat layers until all used.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour, salt and soda together; add to creamed mixture.
Fold in oatmeal and nuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes. Store in airtight container to retain crispness.

title: mom's sloppy joes
directions: Fry hamburg.
Add tomato paste, spices, sugar and vinegar and cook.
Add celery and onion; simmer.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chop broccoli and cauliflower. Refrigerate to chill.
